1
00:00:15,960 --> 00:00:17,880
[ThunderRumbling]

2
00:01:03,080 --> 00:01:06,120
This is Richard Valeriani
reporting live...

3
00:01:06,160 --> 00:01:08,760
for CNN from the French
aircraft carrier Foch...

4
00:01:08,840 --> 00:01:11,000
somewhere in the Mediterranean.

5
00:01:11,080 --> 00:01:13,520
Six days ago,
as the rebellion in Chechnya...

6
00:01:13,600 --> 00:01:16,280
spread to the neighboring Caucasus
republics, the Russian president...

7
00:01:16,360 --> 00:01:19,600
ordered massive bombing strikes
against rebel positions...

8
00:01:19,680 --> 00:01:22,360
around Rutul and Belokany.

9
00:01:22,440 --> 00:01:26,240
Appalled at the loss of human life,
the President of the United States...

10
00:01:26,320 --> 00:01:29,000
joined by the French president
and the British prime minister...

11
00:01:29,040 --> 00:01:31,920
suspended all foreign aid
to Russia.

12
00:01:31,960 --> 00:01:34,840
Ultranationalist leader
Vladimir Radchenko...

13
00:01:34,920 --> 00:01:37,960
denounced the U.S. Pressure
as an act of war...

14
00:01:38,040 --> 00:01:40,520
against the Russian Republic
and Russian sovereignty.

15
00:01:40,560 --> 00:01:43,800
Denouncing his own president
as a U.S. Puppet...

16
00:01:43,880 --> 00:01:48,120
he called on the Russian people
to join him in revolt.

17
00:01:48,200 --> 00:01:51,480
He said, "This brutish and hypocritical
American intervention...

18
00:01:51,560 --> 00:01:53,440
will not go unanswered."

19
00:01:53,520 --> 00:01:56,520
On Tuesday, at 10:00
in the morning Moscow time...

20
00:01:56,600 --> 00:02:01,080
the Russian parliament was suspended
and martial law was declared.

21
00:02:01,160 --> 00:02:03,560
With the government in crisis,
the Russian Republic...

22
00:02:03,640 --> 00:02:07,440
was entering into what can only
be described as a state of civil war.

23
00:02:07,480 --> 00:02:10,760
Then yesterday at dawn,
Radchenko and rebel forces...

24
00:02:10,800 --> 00:02:14,280
seized the region around Vladivostok,
including a naval base...

25
00:02:14,320 --> 00:02:17,480
and a nuclear missile base
housing Russian ICBMs.

26
00:02:17,520 --> 00:02:23,080
As regular Russian military forces
move in to encircle Radchenko...

27
00:02:23,120 --> 00:02:26,520
allied military forces
are in a state of high alert.

28
00:02:26,600 --> 00:02:28,680
These French planes
taking off behind me...

29
00:02:28,720 --> 00:02:32,320
have been deployed near the Caucasus
since the beginning of the crisis...

30
00:02:32,400 --> 00:02:35,360
and a crisis which started
in the Caucasus

31
00:02:35,440 --> 00:02:37,080
has now spread to the Far East...

32
00:02:37,160 --> 00:02:41,280
and appears to be turning into the worst
standoff since the Cuban missile crisis.

33
00:02:42,560 --> 00:02:45,600
This is Richard Valeriani
reporting live for CNN...

34
00:02:45,680 --> 00:02:48,880
from the French aircraft carrier Foch,
somewhere in the Mediterranean.

35
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:57,360
Abracadabra!

36
00:02:57,440 --> 00:03:01,000
- I can't hear you.
- [Screaming] Abracadabra!

37
00:03:01,080 --> 00:03:04,480
[Children Exclaiming]

38
00:03:04,560 --> 00:03:08,200
I need a volunteer
from the audience.

39
00:03:08,240 --> 00:03:10,640
- [Kids] Me! Me!
- Me, me, me!

40
00:03:10,720 --> 00:03:12,960
A brave volunteer.

41
00:03:13,040 --> 00:03:15,280
[Kids] Me! Me! Me!

42
00:03:15,360 --> 00:03:17,760
Preferably...

43
00:03:17,840 --> 00:03:20,800
Preferably somebody who was born
on October 18...

44
00:03:20,880 --> 00:03:23,240
nineteen hundred and ninety.

45
00:03:23,280 --> 00:03:26,560
That's you, honey. That's you.

46
00:03:26,640 --> 00:03:28,680
[Magician] Over here? Over here?

47
00:03:28,760 --> 00:03:32,280
Ahh! You must be the birthday girl.

48
00:03:32,360 --> 00:03:34,400
- What's your name?
- Robin.

49
00:03:34,480 --> 00:03:37,880
[TV] Russian ultranationalist leader,
backed by his rebel army...

50
00:03:37,960 --> 00:03:42,120
threatened nuclear attack
on the United States and Japan.

51
00:03:42,160 --> 00:03:45,040
The threats come as a response
to U.S. Involvement in Chechnya...

52
00:03:45,080 --> 00:03:47,760
and are not considered idle.

53
00:03:47,800 --> 00:03:49,680
Now sit on the board.

54
00:03:49,760 --> 00:03:52,200
And tell me, Robin,
do you believe in magic?

55
00:03:52,240 --> 00:03:54,280
- Where'd he go?
- Good. Because if you believe...

56
00:03:54,320 --> 00:03:56,200
- I'll get him.
- We can suspend you in the air...

57
00:03:56,240 --> 00:03:58,480
- Be right back.
- Without the help of a flying carpet.

58
00:03:58,560 --> 00:04:00,400
Meeting in an emergency session...

59
00:04:00,480 --> 00:04:02,320
You'll miss your daughter's levitation.

60
00:04:02,400 --> 00:04:04,360
While the President is sequestered
with his joint chiefs of staff.

61
00:04:04,400 --> 00:04:08,200
[Automatic Gunfire]

62
00:04:08,240 --> 00:04:11,560
That footage was taken yesterday,
but half an hour ago...

63
00:04:11,640 --> 00:04:14,720
surrounded by hostile forces,
rebel leader Vladimir Radchenko...

64
00:04:14,800 --> 00:04:16,640
Maybe it's not as bad as it looks.

65
00:04:16,720 --> 00:04:20,400
- [Phone Rings]
- Threatened to use nuclear arms
on the United States and Japan...

66
00:04:20,440 --> 00:04:23,880
should anyone, including the Russian
Army, attempt to move in on him.

67
00:04:23,920 --> 00:04:26,200
[Ringing Continues]

68
00:04:26,280 --> 00:04:28,160
- Based on the history of this man...
- [Pager Beeps]

69
00:04:28,240 --> 00:04:30,760
- This can't be viewed as an idle threat.
- [Beeper Continues]

70
00:04:30,840 --> 00:04:33,120
- Sander Vanocur standing by...
- It is.

71
00:04:41,240 --> 00:04:44,000
Commander Hunter.

72
00:05:03,360 --> 00:05:05,680
[Thunder Rumbling]

73
00:05:05,760 --> 00:05:08,440
- [Classical]
- Annapolis.

74
00:05:08,560 --> 00:05:11,320
Five patrols on fast attacks.

75
00:05:11,400 --> 00:05:14,960
Two on boomers;
one as X.O.

76
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:17,920
- [Continues]
- Hmm.

77
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:23,000
A year at...
Excuse me. Harvard?

78
00:05:28,800 --> 00:05:32,680
I talked to your former C.O.
He tells me he tried to adopt you.

79
00:05:34,680 --> 00:05:39,120
As you no doubt heard,
my X.O. Has appendicitis.

80
00:05:39,200 --> 00:05:41,520
He's the best
I ever had.

81
00:05:41,560 --> 00:05:43,720
I need a good man
to fill his spot.

82
00:05:43,800 --> 00:05:46,520
Your name was
at the top of the list.

83
00:05:46,600 --> 00:05:49,040
Well, that's good to know, sir.

84
00:05:50,080 --> 00:05:52,920
It was a short list.

85
00:05:54,840 --> 00:05:57,680
Your interests, Mr. Hunter.
What do you like to do? Do you, uh...

86
00:05:57,760 --> 00:06:01,520
Do you paint, play ball, play
an instrument, ride motorcycles, what?

87
00:06:01,560 --> 00:06:03,920
- I ride horses.
- Horses.

88
00:06:03,960 --> 00:06:06,200
What's the best horse
you ever rode?

89
00:06:06,320 --> 00:06:10,320
- Arabian, sir.
- An Arabian? That's a powerful animal.

90
00:06:10,360 --> 00:06:12,520
- Yes.
- [Chuckles]

91
00:06:12,600 --> 00:06:16,120
- You ever ridden one?
- Me? Are you kidding?

92
00:06:16,160 --> 00:06:19,640
Nah, I couldn't handle an Arabian.
Nah, just give me an old paint.

93
00:06:23,800 --> 00:06:26,160
Yeah, horses are
fascinating animals.

94
00:06:26,200 --> 00:06:28,560
Dumb as fence posts
but very intuitive.

95
00:06:28,600 --> 00:06:31,680
In that way, they're not too different
from high school girls.

96
00:06:31,760 --> 00:06:34,000
They might not have
a brain in their head...

97
00:06:34,040 --> 00:06:36,920
but they do know
all the boys want to fuck 'em.

98
00:06:37,040 --> 00:06:40,840
Don't have to be able to read Ulysses
to know where they're comin' from.

99
00:06:40,920 --> 00:06:43,680
- No, sir.
- [Barking]

100
00:06:47,920 --> 00:06:50,480
He approves of you.

101
00:06:50,560 --> 00:06:53,600
Jack Russells.
Smartest dogs alive.

102
00:06:53,680 --> 00:06:57,160
Name's Bear.
Goes everyplace with me.

103
00:07:02,240 --> 00:07:06,320
Well, welcome aboard
the Alabama, son.

104
00:07:06,360 --> 00:07:08,280
- Do me proud.
- I will, sir.

105
00:07:08,320 --> 00:07:11,480
- Congratulations, Mr. Hunter.
- Thank you.

106
00:07:11,600 --> 00:07:14,720
If one Russian citizen
is killed...

107
00:07:14,800 --> 00:07:16,640
and I am president...

108
00:07:16,720 --> 00:07:22,320
then I will kill 900,000 of the people
who are responsible.

109
00:07:22,360 --> 00:07:25,600
- You'd use nuclear weapons?
- Yes, I would hit them...
- Attention!

110
00:07:25,680 --> 00:07:27,520
With nuclear weapons.

111
00:07:27,600 --> 00:07:29,440
- At ease. Be seated.
- [Reporter] Sir, such talk
is highly inflammatory.

112
00:07:29,520 --> 00:07:33,160
[Radchenko] My dear young lady,
I do not engage in "talk."

113
00:07:33,240 --> 00:07:37,240
These are serious threats, which I hope
to be in the position to carry out.

114
00:07:37,280 --> 00:07:40,240
I take it you've seen enough?

115
00:07:40,320 --> 00:07:44,240
Gentlemen, after a nice little vacation,
looks like we're back at it again.

116
00:07:44,320 --> 00:07:48,120
I hope you enjoyed the peace, because
as of now, we're back in business.

117
00:07:48,200 --> 00:07:51,280
In the good old days of Cold War, the
Russians could always be depended on...

118
00:07:51,320 --> 00:07:54,760
doing whatever is in
their own best interests.

119
00:07:54,840 --> 00:07:59,240
But this Radchenko's playing a whole new
ball game with a whole new set of rules.

120
00:07:59,320 --> 00:08:01,080
Now I've heard people talk...

121
00:08:01,120 --> 00:08:03,880
but I don't think this man's talking
to get his picture in the paper.

122
00:08:03,960 --> 00:08:07,960
He seems to have a serious weed
up his ass and a legitimate gripe.

123
00:08:08,040 --> 00:08:11,240
Always a dangerous combination.
And I think he's capable...

124
00:08:11,320 --> 00:08:13,960
of doing every damn thing
he says he's going to do.

125
00:08:14,040 --> 00:08:18,320
That's why we have to go out there
and give the man a moment of pause.

126
00:08:18,400 --> 00:08:21,720
So ends theory.
Thus, let us begin the facts.

127
00:08:21,800 --> 00:08:24,760
We've been informed by the NSA...

128
00:08:24,880 --> 00:08:27,240
that an entire rebel corps
of the Russian Army is involved.

129
00:08:27,320 --> 00:08:30,560
That's four armored divisions
numbering 60,000 men.

130
00:08:30,640 --> 00:08:32,480
There seems to be
massive defections.

131
00:08:32,560 --> 00:08:36,400
Vladimir seems to be winning the hearts
and minds of the Russian soldiers.

132
00:08:36,440 --> 00:08:38,840
- Admiral.
- Thank you.

133
00:08:45,080 --> 00:08:48,920
They've seized the region by the Chinese
and North Korean borders.

134
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:51,240
That includes a submarine base...

135
00:08:51,320 --> 00:08:53,640
from which they've surged
four Akula-class attack subs.

136
00:08:53,720 --> 00:08:57,040
They have acquired
a nuclear base at Artem...

137
00:08:57,120 --> 00:09:01,960
that houses 25 hardened silos
for Russian ICBMs...

138
00:09:02,040 --> 00:09:04,760
armed with up to
ten warheads apiece.

139
00:09:04,800 --> 00:09:08,600
Now the Russian government has
assured us that talks are underway.

140
00:09:08,640 --> 00:09:13,040
They claim that Radchenko forces
do not possess the launch codes.

141
00:09:13,120 --> 00:09:15,120
But if Radchenko
were to crack them...

142
00:09:15,200 --> 00:09:17,680
they could launch against
our west coast direct...

143
00:09:17,760 --> 00:09:20,920
or come in over the Pole,
take out Washington and New York.

144
00:09:20,960 --> 00:09:23,560
[Admiral] The Commander-in-Chief...

145
00:09:23,640 --> 00:09:25,960
has directed U.S. Military forces...

146
00:09:26,040 --> 00:09:28,880
to set DEFCON four.

147
00:09:28,920 --> 00:09:31,400
We've been ordered
to get underway at 0600 hours...

148
00:09:31,480 --> 00:09:35,280
to assume alert coverage, mid-Pacific,
the Far Eastern TVD target package.

149
00:09:35,360 --> 00:09:37,240
Please keep your men informed.

150
00:09:37,280 --> 00:09:39,600
Lieutenant Commander Hunter
is our new X.O.

151
00:09:39,640 --> 00:09:44,080
Please bring him up to speed on
ship's personnel and supplies. Admiral?

152
00:09:44,160 --> 00:09:46,200
- No, that's it.
- On your feet.

153
00:09:52,440 --> 00:09:55,640
- [Door Closes]
- [Men Muttering]

154
00:09:55,720 --> 00:09:58,240
- Here we go again, Commander.
- Thank you.

155
00:09:58,320 --> 00:10:01,880
You bet. Hey, Bobby.
This is Bobby Dougherty. He's Supplies.

156
00:10:01,960 --> 00:10:04,120
- Pleasure, Dougherty.
- Billy Linkletter, TSO.

157
00:10:04,160 --> 00:10:07,000
- Mr. Linkletter.
- Commander.
- And you know Darik.

158
00:10:07,040 --> 00:10:09,360
- Yes. Westergaurd. Long time no see.
- How's Julia?

159
00:10:09,400 --> 00:10:11,280
- She's excellent.
- Good.

160
00:10:11,320 --> 00:10:13,880
- And Roy Zimmer, Communications.
- Welcome aboard.

161
00:10:13,960 --> 00:10:16,960
- Thank you.
- We served together on the Baton Rouge.

162
00:10:17,040 --> 00:10:22,320
- Twice.
- That's right. We're lucky to have him.

163
00:10:22,360 --> 00:10:25,720
- I think his dog gave me
the final seal of approval.
- He's crazy about that dog.

164
00:10:25,800 --> 00:10:28,840
Takes him everywhere. The Navy looks
the other way 'cause he's Ramsey.

165
00:10:28,920 --> 00:10:32,560
Navy looks the other way
'cause he's one of the few skippers
left who've seen combat.

166
00:10:32,600 --> 00:10:35,840
- He took SEALS into Panama in '89.
- Tomahawks in the Gulf in '91.

167
00:10:35,920 --> 00:10:38,640
- Took out eight or nine X.O. S in '94?
- Ouch.

168
00:10:38,680 --> 00:10:41,720
- Last one caught what? Appendicitis?
- Yeah, right.

169
00:10:43,200 --> 00:10:45,080
[Man Shouting]

170
00:10:48,040 --> 00:10:51,080
- The Enemy Below.
- Robert Mitchum.

171
00:10:51,160 --> 00:10:53,000
- And?
- And what?

172
00:10:53,080 --> 00:10:55,240
- Robert Mitchum.
- Incomplete answer.

173
00:10:55,320 --> 00:10:57,960
- The German guy with the white hair?
- Yeah. What's his name?

174
00:10:58,040 --> 00:11:00,880
- Who was it?
- Curt Jurgens.

175
00:11:00,960 --> 00:11:05,720
[Couple Shouting]

176
00:11:11,160 --> 00:11:13,200
Hardy Kruger.

177
00:11:13,280 --> 00:11:15,160
[Laughing] No way.

178
00:11:15,240 --> 00:11:17,920
- Robert Shaw in his Nazi period.
- [Laughs]

179
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:20,920
Question is invalid.
We're even.

180
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:23,000
- Whoo.
- How you doin'?

181
00:11:23,080 --> 00:11:26,200
- I'm fine. Thanks.
- Good. Address me as "sir"
when you speak to me!

182
00:11:26,280 --> 00:11:28,480
Stand at attention, sailor!

183
00:11:28,560 --> 00:11:31,240
Is he gonna fit in the sub?

184
00:11:31,320 --> 00:11:33,200
Doubtful.

185
00:11:33,240 --> 00:11:36,720
Who played the German sub commander
in The Enemy Below with Robert Mitchum?

186
00:11:36,760 --> 00:11:39,680
- Was it Curt Jurgens or Hardy Kruger?
- Sir...

187
00:11:39,760 --> 00:11:42,800
Wrong answer!
Drop down and give me 20! Now!

188
00:11:42,840 --> 00:11:46,920
- Move! Move!
- One. [Straining] Two.

189
00:11:47,000 --> 00:11:49,880
- Run Silent, Run Deep.
- [Sailor] Three.

190
00:11:49,960 --> 00:11:52,400
The guy with the ears
and a little moustache.

191
00:11:52,440 --> 00:11:55,840
- Cary Grant.
- [Grunts]

192
00:11:56,880 --> 00:12:00,000
I'm worried about "T."

193
00:12:00,080 --> 00:12:02,120
[Whining]

194
00:12:02,200 --> 00:12:04,680
- Why?
- She doesn't know what's goin' on.

195
00:12:04,760 --> 00:12:07,680
I think she thinks
I'm goin' away forever.

196
00:12:08,800 --> 00:12:11,480
- I'll take care of her.
- You will?

197
00:12:11,520 --> 00:12:13,400
- Yeah.
- You promise?

198
00:12:13,440 --> 00:12:15,320
I promise.

199
00:12:17,400 --> 00:12:19,720
- I love you, Dad.
- I love you too, son.

200
00:12:19,800 --> 00:12:21,840
[Kissing]

201
00:12:23,720 --> 00:12:25,600
Okay.

202
00:12:28,800 --> 00:12:30,760
[Sighs] You know
I don't know what to say.

203
00:12:30,840 --> 00:12:33,120
Just say good-bye.

204
00:12:40,040 --> 00:12:42,000
See you in my dreams.

205
00:12:43,360 --> 00:12:45,760
Give me a kiss.

206
00:13:05,440 --> 00:13:07,320
- Davis.
- How you doin', sir?

207
00:13:30,640 --> 00:13:32,600
Crew present and
accounted for, sir.

208
00:13:34,840 --> 00:13:36,760
Little ducks...

209
00:13:37,800 --> 00:13:39,960
there's trouble
in Russia.

210
00:13:40,960 --> 00:13:42,840
So they called us.

211
00:13:44,280 --> 00:13:47,200
We're going over there
and bringing...

212
00:13:47,280 --> 00:13:49,720
the most lethal killing machine
ever devised.

213
00:13:51,320 --> 00:13:53,320
We're capable...

214
00:13:53,400 --> 00:13:56,000
of launching
more firepower...

215
00:13:56,080 --> 00:13:59,560
than has ever been released
in the history of war.

216
00:14:01,080 --> 00:14:02,920
For one purpose alone:

217
00:14:04,640 --> 00:14:06,480
To keep our country safe.

218
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:11,520
We constitute the front line...

219
00:14:11,600 --> 00:14:14,400
and the last line of defense.

220
00:14:14,440 --> 00:14:16,640
[Thunder Rumbling]

221
00:14:19,080 --> 00:14:22,480
I expect and demand...

222
00:14:22,560 --> 00:14:24,400
your very best.

223
00:14:25,960 --> 00:14:29,600
Anything less, you should have
joined the Air Force.

224
00:14:29,680 --> 00:14:32,800
[Men Laughing]

225
00:14:34,200 --> 00:14:37,800
This might be our
Commander-in-Chief's Navy...

226
00:14:37,880 --> 00:14:40,120
but this is my boat.

227
00:14:40,160 --> 00:14:43,040
And all I ask is that
you keep up with me.

228
00:14:43,120 --> 00:14:45,920
And if you can't...

229
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:49,800
that strange sensation you'll be feeling
in the seat of your pants...

230
00:14:49,880 --> 00:14:52,280
will be my boot in your ass.

231
00:15:08,000 --> 00:15:10,040
- Mr. Cob?
- Yes, sir!

232
00:15:10,120 --> 00:15:13,240
You're aware of the name of this ship,
aren't you, Mr. Cob?

233
00:15:13,280 --> 00:15:15,200
Very aware, sir!

234
00:15:15,240 --> 00:15:17,240
It bears a proud name,
doesn't it, Mr. Cob?

235
00:15:17,280 --> 00:15:19,120
Very proud, sir!

236
00:15:19,200 --> 00:15:22,680
- It represents fine people.
- Very fine people, sir!

237
00:15:22,760 --> 00:15:26,560
- Who live in a fine, outstanding state.
- [Cob] Outstanding, sir!

238
00:15:26,640 --> 00:15:29,040
In the greatest country
in the entire world.

239
00:15:29,120 --> 00:15:31,560
[Cob] In the entire world, sir.

240
00:15:31,640 --> 00:15:35,160
- And what is that name, Mr. Cob?
- Alabama, sir!

241
00:15:35,200 --> 00:15:37,800
- And what do we say?
- [Both] Go, 'Bama!

242
00:15:37,880 --> 00:15:39,480
[All] Roll tide!

243
00:15:39,560 --> 00:15:42,200
Chief of the boat,
dismiss the crew.

244
00:15:42,240 --> 00:15:44,200
Dismiss the crew.
Aye, aye, sir.

245
00:15:44,280 --> 00:15:49,080
Crew! Department heads!
Attend to your departments!

246
00:15:49,120 --> 00:15:52,440
- Fall out!
- [Men Cheering]

247
00:16:18,240 --> 00:16:22,160
Here. Part of your qualification
for command.

248
00:16:23,600 --> 00:16:25,760
[Sighs]

249
00:16:25,840 --> 00:16:30,360
The last breath of polluted air
for the next 65 days.

250
00:16:30,440 --> 00:16:32,320
Gonna miss it.

251
00:16:32,360 --> 00:16:35,400
I don't trust air I can't see.
[Chuckles]

252
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:49,520
[Ramsey] This is my favorite part.
Right here, right now.

253
00:17:01,080 --> 00:17:02,920
Bravo, Hunter.

254
00:17:03,000 --> 00:17:04,840
Sir?

255
00:17:06,080 --> 00:17:08,640
You knew to shut up
and enjoy the view.

256
00:17:08,720 --> 00:17:11,080
Most eggheads want
to talk it away.

257
00:17:12,320 --> 00:17:15,120
Your stock just went up
a couple of points.

258
00:17:15,200 --> 00:17:17,240
Thank you, sir.

259
00:17:17,320 --> 00:17:20,000
Allow me to give you
a tiny bit of advice.

260
00:17:20,080 --> 00:17:21,960
If you want
your own boat someday...

261
00:17:22,040 --> 00:17:26,200
the very worst thing you can do is worry
about yourself or try to impress me.

262
00:17:26,240 --> 00:17:29,800
I can't stand save-asses,
and I won't abide kiss-asses.

263
00:17:29,880 --> 00:17:33,320
You keep your priorities straight:
Your mission and your men.

264
00:17:37,920 --> 00:17:39,960
How you like that cigar?

265
00:17:41,840 --> 00:17:43,680
- It's good, sir.
- It's your first.

266
00:17:43,760 --> 00:17:45,880
Yeah.
[Coughing]

267
00:17:45,920 --> 00:17:49,800
[Chuckling] Don't like it too much.
They're more expensive than drugs.

268
00:17:50,960 --> 00:17:53,000
X.O., take her down.

269
00:17:53,080 --> 00:17:55,320
Take her down.
Aye, sir.

270
00:17:55,360 --> 00:17:58,480
Control/Bridge:
Sounding.

271
00:17:58,560 --> 00:18:00,840
Bridge/Control:
Sounding 130 fathoms.

272
00:18:00,920 --> 00:18:05,240
[Men's Choir Singing]

273
00:18:07,400 --> 00:18:10,360
- Lookouts, clear the bridge.
- Clear the bridge. Aye, sir.

274
00:18:10,440 --> 00:18:12,360
Officer of the deck,
prepare to dive.

275
00:18:12,440 --> 00:18:15,040
- Captain down.
- Captain is down.

276
00:18:15,120 --> 00:18:17,480
[Dive Alarm Ringing]

277
00:18:17,560 --> 00:18:19,800
[Men's Choir]

278
00:18:19,840 --> 00:18:22,840
- X.O. Down.
- X.O. Is down.

279
00:18:22,880 --> 00:18:27,640
[Choir Continues]

280
00:18:35,720 --> 00:18:38,080
- Submerge the ship.
- Diving Officer, submerge the ship.

281
00:18:38,120 --> 00:18:41,920
- Make your depth 150 feet.
- Make my depth 150 feet. Aye, sir.

282
00:18:42,000 --> 00:18:45,640
Chief of the watch,
on the 1MC, dive, dive!

283
00:19:02,920 --> 00:19:05,120
Make your depth 150 feet.

284
00:19:05,200 --> 00:19:08,160
Five degree down bubble.

285
00:19:48,160 --> 00:19:50,880
- [Zimmer] I don't understand.
- [Dougherty] You don't understand?

286
00:19:50,960 --> 00:19:55,080
Radchenko is a fanatic, okay?
He's a potential Hitler.

287
00:19:55,160 --> 00:19:57,320
- Somebody should just shoot him.
- I have no problem with that.

288
00:19:57,400 --> 00:20:00,120
- Good.
- Well, it's fanatics who make history.

289
00:20:00,200 --> 00:20:02,280
- Colonel Patton was a fanatic.
- That's what made him great.

290
00:20:02,360 --> 00:20:04,440
[Linkletter]
You think this guy is Patton?

291
00:20:04,520 --> 00:20:07,520
He's a dangerous lunatic, threatening
nuclear war, and he means it.

292
00:20:07,560 --> 00:20:10,560
What's that make us, since we're the
only nation to ever drop a nuclear bomb?

293
00:20:10,640 --> 00:20:13,120
It makes us a prime target.
There's a half a dozen...

294
00:20:13,160 --> 00:20:16,560
other Third World countries with
atom bombs who'd love to drop one on us.

295
00:20:16,640 --> 00:20:18,520
[Dougherty] That's right.
That's why we should drop one on them.

296
00:20:18,600 --> 00:20:21,600
Are you a communist? You have a problem
with us dropping nuclear bombs on Japan?

297
00:20:21,640 --> 00:20:26,080
- Shut up, Dougherty.
- You think it was a mistake, Mr. Hunter?

298
00:20:26,160 --> 00:20:27,520
Sir?

299
00:20:27,560 --> 00:20:30,120
Using the bomb
on Hiroshima and Nagasaki.

300
00:20:33,040 --> 00:20:37,400
- Well, if I thought that,
sir, I wouldn't be here.
- [Ramsey Laughing]

301
00:20:37,480 --> 00:20:40,120
- Interesting way you put that.
- How'd I put it, sir?

302
00:20:42,080 --> 00:20:44,080
Very carefully.

303
00:20:44,160 --> 00:20:47,560
[Men Laughing]

304
00:20:47,640 --> 00:20:49,880
You do qualify your remarks.

305
00:20:49,960 --> 00:20:52,000
Somebody asked me if we
should have bombed Japan...

306
00:20:52,080 --> 00:20:56,080
a simple, "Yes, by all means, sir.
Drop that fucker. Twice."

307
00:20:56,160 --> 00:20:59,000
- [Men Laughing]
- I don't mean to suggest...

308
00:20:59,080 --> 00:21:00,960
that you're indecisive,
Mr. Hunter.

309
00:21:01,000 --> 00:21:02,880
Not at all.

310
00:21:02,920 --> 00:21:06,560
Just, um... complicated.

311
00:21:06,600 --> 00:21:08,440
[Chuckles]

312
00:21:08,520 --> 00:21:12,240
Of course, that's the way
the Navy wants you.

313
00:21:12,320 --> 00:21:15,040
Me, they wanted simple.

314
00:21:15,080 --> 00:21:18,960
- Well, you certainly fooled them, sir.
- [Laughs]

315
00:21:19,040 --> 00:21:20,880
Be careful there, Mr. Hunter.

316
00:21:20,960 --> 00:21:24,720
It's all I got to rely on:
Bein' a simpleminded son of a bitch.

317
00:21:24,800 --> 00:21:27,840
Rickhover gave me
my command...

318
00:21:27,880 --> 00:21:30,920
a checklist, a target
and a button to push.

319
00:21:31,000 --> 00:21:32,840
All I had to know
is how to push it.

320
00:21:32,920 --> 00:21:36,880
They'd tell me when.
They seem to want you to know why.

321
00:21:36,960 --> 00:21:40,480
I would hope they'd want
us all to know why, sir.

322
00:21:43,600 --> 00:21:45,200
At the Naval War College...

323
00:21:45,280 --> 00:21:48,200
it was metallurgy and nuclear reactors,
not 19th-century philosophy.

324
00:21:48,280 --> 00:21:49,920
[Stifled Laugh]

325
00:21:50,000 --> 00:21:53,200
"War is a continuation
of politics by other means."

326
00:21:53,280 --> 00:21:56,320
Von Clausewitz.

327
00:21:56,360 --> 00:22:00,080
I think, sir, that what he was actually
trying to say was a little more...

328
00:22:00,160 --> 00:22:03,360
- Complicated?
- [Men Laughing]

329
00:22:07,080 --> 00:22:10,200
Yes, the purpose of war is
to serve a political end...

330
00:22:10,280 --> 00:22:12,400
but the true nature of war
is to serve itself.

331
00:22:12,480 --> 00:22:15,600
[Laughing]
I'm very impressed.

332
00:22:15,680 --> 00:22:18,120
In other words, the sailor
most likely to win the war...

333
00:22:18,200 --> 00:22:21,040
is the one most willing to part
company with the politicians...

334
00:22:21,120 --> 00:22:24,080
and ignore everything except
the destruction of the enemy.

335
00:22:24,160 --> 00:22:26,240
You'd agree with that.

336
00:22:26,320 --> 00:22:30,640
I'd agree that, uh, that's what
Clausewitz was trying to say.

337
00:22:30,720 --> 00:22:32,960
But you wouldn't agree with it?

338
00:22:33,040 --> 00:22:37,080
No, sir, I do not. No, I just think
that in the nuclear world...

339
00:22:39,080 --> 00:22:40,960
the true enemy
can't be destroyed.

340
00:22:44,600 --> 00:22:48,160
[Chuckling, Tapping Glass]
Attention on deck.

341
00:22:48,200 --> 00:22:51,560
Von Clausewitz will now tell us
exactly who the real enemy is.

342
00:22:51,640 --> 00:22:53,960
- [Laughing]
- Von?

343
00:22:54,040 --> 00:22:57,040
[Men Laughing]

344
00:23:00,680 --> 00:23:04,080
In my humble opinion,
in the nuclear world...

345
00:23:04,160 --> 00:23:06,520
the true enemy
is war itself.

346
00:23:17,520 --> 00:23:20,680
[Martha And The Vandellas]
Everywhere I go your face I see

347
00:23:20,760 --> 00:23:23,000
Every step I take

348
00:23:23,120 --> 00:23:25,560
- You take with me
- [Singing Along With Tape]

349
00:23:25,640 --> 00:23:29,200
Nowhere to run to, baby

350
00:23:29,280 --> 00:23:32,080
Nowhere to hide

351
00:23:32,160 --> 00:23:36,320
Got nowhere to run, baby

352
00:23:36,400 --> 00:23:38,240
Nowhere to hide

353
00:23:39,600 --> 00:23:42,360
I know you're no good for me

354
00:23:42,440 --> 00:23:46,920
But free of you
I'll never be, baby

355
00:23:55,280 --> 00:23:57,800
[Yelling]

356
00:23:57,880 --> 00:23:59,680
Move!

357
00:24:11,640 --> 00:24:14,960
Fire in the galley! Chief of the watch,
sound the general alarm!

358
00:24:15,040 --> 00:24:17,760
[Alarm Ringing]

359
00:24:37,960 --> 00:24:40,480
[P.A.] Forward damage control, bring
additional fire extinguishers to the...

360
00:24:40,560 --> 00:24:43,840
- [Coughing]
- Fire's out of control. He's hurtin'.

361
00:24:43,920 --> 00:24:46,760
- You hit the kill switch?
- Couldn't get to it. Too hot.

362
00:24:46,840 --> 00:24:49,480
[Fire Roaring, Men Shouting]

363
00:24:51,520 --> 00:24:55,040
[Alarm Ringing]

364
00:24:57,200 --> 00:24:59,040
[Shouting]

365
00:25:05,720 --> 00:25:08,680
[P.A.] Attention, all hands.
Fire has been contained.

366
00:25:08,720 --> 00:25:12,680
Damage control party,
assess damage and report to Control.

367
00:25:12,720 --> 00:25:15,680
- Initiate weapons system readiness test.
- Aye, sir.

368
00:25:15,760 --> 00:25:17,800
[Tapping Keyboard]

369
00:25:20,560 --> 00:25:25,080
All right, station a reflash watch.
This thing could flare back up again.

370
00:25:25,160 --> 00:25:28,040
[Computer Beeping]

371
00:25:28,120 --> 00:25:31,200
[Beeping]

372
00:25:31,280 --> 00:25:34,920
Conn/Radio: We are receiving
flash traffic emergency action message.

373
00:25:34,960 --> 00:25:37,680
Recommend alert one.
Recommend alert one.

374
00:25:37,760 --> 00:25:41,600
Alert one. Man battle stations missile
for weapons systems readiness test.

375
00:25:41,680 --> 00:25:43,960
- Spin up all missiles.
- What the hell is he runnin'
a missile drill now for?

376
00:25:44,040 --> 00:25:46,080
- You're in charge.
- Aye, sir.

377
00:25:46,160 --> 00:25:48,880
[P.A.] Man battle stations missiles
for weapons system readiness test.

378
00:25:48,960 --> 00:25:51,480
Spin up all missiles.
This is an exercise.

379
00:25:51,560 --> 00:25:54,360
- [Men Chattering]
- Captain's in Control.

380
00:26:01,680 --> 00:26:03,520
I agree.
The message is properly formatted.

381
00:26:03,600 --> 00:26:06,240
Sir, we have a properly formatted
emergency action message...

382
00:26:06,320 --> 00:26:08,280
for weapons system
readiness test, sir.

383
00:26:08,360 --> 00:26:10,400
- I concur, sir.
- Where's the X.O.?

384
00:26:13,360 --> 00:26:15,760
- Sir.
- Good of you to make it, Mr. Hunter.

385
00:26:15,840 --> 00:26:17,760
Get the authenticator.

386
00:26:17,840 --> 00:26:20,120
[Panting]
Get the authenticator.

387
00:26:22,080 --> 00:26:24,600
[Coughing]

388
00:26:31,600 --> 00:26:33,600
Let's go.

389
00:26:39,120 --> 00:26:40,960
Sir, request permission
to authenticate.

390
00:26:41,040 --> 00:26:43,560
Permission granted.
Authenticate.

391
00:26:46,520 --> 00:26:51,040
"Alpha, Alpha, Bravo,
Echo, Charlie, Zulu, Tango."

392
00:26:51,120 --> 00:26:55,760
"Alpha, Alpha, Bravo, Echo,
Charlie, Zulu, Tango."

393
00:26:55,840 --> 00:26:57,920
- Captain, message is authentic.
- I concur, sir.

394
00:26:58,000 --> 00:27:00,600
- I agree.
- Message is authentic.

395
00:27:00,680 --> 00:27:02,520
Sir, your captain's
missile key.

396
00:27:09,520 --> 00:27:13,680
Set condition 1Sq for WSRT. This is
the captain. This is an exercise.

397
00:27:13,760 --> 00:27:17,160
Set condition 1Sq for WSRT.
This is the X.O. This is an exercise.

398
00:27:18,400 --> 00:27:21,560
Captain, that fire in the galley
could still flare...

399
00:27:21,640 --> 00:27:24,680
Now is not the time.
Make your depth 150 feet. All stop.

400
00:27:24,720 --> 00:27:27,760
Make my depth 150 feet.
All stop. Aye, sir.

401
00:27:27,840 --> 00:27:29,960
Weapons/Conn:
Simulate pressurizing, all tubes.

402
00:27:30,040 --> 00:27:33,000
Weapons/Conn:
Simulate pressurizing, all tubes.

403
00:27:33,080 --> 00:27:36,040
Conn/Weapons: Simulate pressurizing,
all missiles. Aye, aye, sir.

404
00:27:36,120 --> 00:27:38,000
Simulate pressurizing,
all missiles.

405
00:27:38,040 --> 00:27:41,040
Simulate pressurizing,
all missiles. Aye.

406
00:27:41,120 --> 00:27:43,000
[Beeps]

407
00:27:44,240 --> 00:27:46,160
All stations, proceed to 1Sq.

408
00:27:46,240 --> 00:27:49,480
Ready all missiles for launch.
Come on, guys. Let's go!

409
00:27:50,440 --> 00:27:52,280
Weapons/Captain:

410
00:27:52,360 --> 00:27:54,960
Report approximate time
for 1Sq.

411
00:27:55,040 --> 00:27:59,080
Captain/Weapons: Approximate time
to weapons system 1Sq:

412
00:27:59,120 --> 00:28:01,520
Fourteen minutes, sir.

413
00:28:01,600 --> 00:28:04,440
Ship is at launch depth.
Ready to hover, sir.

414
00:28:04,520 --> 00:28:06,920
- Very well. Commence hovering.
- Commence hovering. Aye, sir.

415
00:28:07,000 --> 00:28:10,840
Control/Sick Bay: Chief Petty Officer
Marichek is undergoing cardiac arrest.

416
00:28:10,920 --> 00:28:15,240
- We're beginning CPR.
- Chief of the watch, on the 1MC.

417
00:28:15,320 --> 00:28:17,240
Gentlemen, may I have
your attention, please?

418
00:28:17,320 --> 00:28:19,680
We've received word that a shipmate
is experiencing a medical problem.

419
00:28:19,760 --> 00:28:24,440
We're terminating the drill. Mr.
Mahoney, take the conn. I'm going below.

420
00:28:24,520 --> 00:28:27,080
- X.O.
- [Mahoney] Aye, sir. I have the conn.

421
00:28:32,160 --> 00:28:34,280
Clear.

422
00:28:34,360 --> 00:28:37,000
Clear.

423
00:28:50,600 --> 00:28:52,440
It's okay, Chief.

424
00:28:53,960 --> 00:28:56,440
Thank you, sir.
Sorry, sir.

425
00:29:16,160 --> 00:29:17,200
[Classical]

426
00:29:17,200 --> 00:29:18,960
[Classical]

427
00:29:20,960 --> 00:29:23,080
[Softly] Hiya, boy.
Hiya, hiya, hiya.

428
00:29:23,120 --> 00:29:26,440
How ya doin'?
Oh, boy. Yeah.

429
00:29:28,560 --> 00:29:32,520
So, Mr. Hunter, do you think
I was wrong to run that drill?

430
00:29:32,600 --> 00:29:34,480
Not necessarily, sir.

431
00:29:34,520 --> 00:29:37,200
- Do you think I got that man killed?
- No, sir.

432
00:29:37,280 --> 00:29:41,040
One thing had nothing to do
with the other. It was an accident.

433
00:29:41,120 --> 00:29:43,680
- Would you have run the drill?
- No, sir, I wouldn't have.

434
00:29:43,760 --> 00:29:45,000
Why not?

435
00:29:45,080 --> 00:29:47,360
The fire in the galley
could have flared back up.

436
00:29:47,440 --> 00:29:51,280
- I would have seen to it first, sir.
- I'm sure you would have.

437
00:29:51,360 --> 00:29:55,600
Me, on the other hand, I tend to think
that's the best time to run a drill.

438
00:29:55,680 --> 00:29:57,880
Confusion on the ship
is nothing to fear.

439
00:29:57,960 --> 00:30:01,120
It should be taken advantage of.

440
00:30:01,200 --> 00:30:05,160
Lest you forget, Mr. Hunter, we are
a ship of war, designed for battle.

441
00:30:05,240 --> 00:30:09,800
You don't just fight battles
when everything is hunky-dory.

442
00:30:09,840 --> 00:30:13,360
What'd you think, son? I was just
some crazy old coot putting everyone...

443
00:30:13,440 --> 00:30:15,280
in harm's way
as I yell "yee-haw"?

444
00:30:15,360 --> 00:30:18,520
That was not
my first thought, sir.

445
00:30:18,600 --> 00:30:22,400
But there's no excuse. At the time
I was fighting the fire in the galley...

446
00:30:22,480 --> 00:30:25,160
I did not agree
with your call, sir.

447
00:30:27,720 --> 00:30:29,560
Take a seat.

448
00:30:34,600 --> 00:30:36,840
[Sighs]

449
00:30:39,760 --> 00:30:43,160
Just so we understand
each other...

450
00:30:43,240 --> 00:30:46,320
I don't have any problems
with questions or doubts.

451
00:30:46,400 --> 00:30:50,120
As I said to you before, I'm not
seeking the company of kiss-asses.

452
00:30:50,160 --> 00:30:53,320
When you got somethin' to say to me,
you say it in private.

453
00:30:53,360 --> 00:30:57,440
And if privacy doesn't permit itself,
then you bite your fucking tongue.

454
00:30:58,880 --> 00:31:01,640
- Are we clear about that, Commander?
- As a bell, sir.

455
00:31:02,960 --> 00:31:05,160
Those sailors out there
are just boys...

456
00:31:05,200 --> 00:31:08,680
boys who are training to do
a terrible and unthinkable thing,
and if that ever occurs...

457
00:31:08,760 --> 00:31:11,720
the only reassurance they'll have
that they're doing the proper thing...

458
00:31:11,800 --> 00:31:15,600
is gonna derive from their unqualified
belief in the unified chain of command.

459
00:31:15,640 --> 00:31:19,760
That means we don't question each
other's motives in front of the crew.

460
00:31:19,840 --> 00:31:22,480
It means we don't
undermine each other.

461
00:31:22,560 --> 00:31:24,480
It means in a missile drill...

462
00:31:24,560 --> 00:31:28,080
they hear your voice right after mine,
without hesitation.

463
00:31:30,160 --> 00:31:32,720
- Do you agree with that policy, sailor?
- Absolutely, sir.

464
00:31:35,120 --> 00:31:39,000
We're here to preserve democracy,
not to practice it.

465
00:31:41,800 --> 00:31:45,760
There'll be a memorial service in
the enlisted men's mess at 1100 hours.

466
00:31:45,840 --> 00:31:48,200
- Go see to it.
- Aye, aye, sir.

467
00:31:48,280 --> 00:31:51,120
Oh, Hunter.

468
00:31:51,200 --> 00:31:53,040
Short of the outbreak
of World War III...

469
00:31:53,120 --> 00:31:57,240
the ship sinking or being
