00:48:27,480 --> 00:48:30,320
Very well.
Float the buoy.

707
00:48:30,360 --> 00:48:32,920
Chief of the watch,
float the buoy.

708
00:48:33,000 --> 00:48:35,320
Float the radio buoy.
Aye, sir.

709
00:48:42,240 --> 00:48:46,800
[Chief Of The Watch]
Radio buoy deploying, sir.
Tension 2,000 pounds.

710
00:48:48,520 --> 00:48:51,400
Very well.

711
00:48:51,480 --> 00:48:55,360
Conn/Weapons: Estimated time to 1Sq:
8 minutes, 30 seconds, sir.

712
00:48:56,920 --> 00:49:00,720
[Metal Grinding]

713
00:49:00,800 --> 00:49:03,400
- [Panel Beeping]
- The winch!

714
00:49:03,480 --> 00:49:07,880
- Conn/Sonar: We have a sound short
from the buoy winch!
- Stop the goddamn winch!

715
00:49:07,960 --> 00:49:10,480
- [Grinding Stops]
- Winch is stopped, sir!

716
00:49:12,600 --> 00:49:14,160
Goddamn it.

717
00:49:25,240 --> 00:49:27,480
TSO, is that sound
still out there?

718
00:49:27,520 --> 00:49:30,480
- Sonar/TSO:
Is that sound still out there?
- [Faint Radio Transmission]

719
00:49:30,560 --> 00:49:33,000
Sound's gone, sir.

720
00:49:47,960 --> 00:49:50,960
- [Sonar Bleeping]
- I'm getting something.

721
00:49:55,200 --> 00:49:57,240
- [Bleeping Continues]
- Sup, he's comin' around!

722
00:49:57,320 --> 00:50:00,600
Conn/Sonar: The Akula's
turning toward, sir!

723
00:50:02,320 --> 00:50:04,960
Conn/Sonar:
Torpedo in the water! Bearing 241!

724
00:50:06,520 --> 00:50:09,480
Conn/Sonar: Second torpedo
in the water! Bearing 242!

725
00:50:09,560 --> 00:50:11,280
All ahead flank!
Right full rudder!

726
00:50:16,800 --> 00:50:19,160
Conn/Sonar:
3,000 yards and closing, sir!

727
00:50:19,240 --> 00:50:21,080
Maneuvering/Conn:
Cavitate! Cavitate!

728
00:50:27,000 --> 00:50:28,840
- Sound the collision alarm!
- Sound collision alarm! Aye, sir!

729
00:50:28,920 --> 00:50:31,480
- [Rivetti] 2,500 yards.
- Rig ship for impact!

730
00:50:31,560 --> 00:50:34,840
Hang onto your ass, gentlemen!
2,000 yards.

731
00:50:37,720 --> 00:50:40,240
1,500 yards.

732
00:50:40,320 --> 00:50:44,240
Bearing 070! 071!
1,200 yards!

733
00:50:48,920 --> 00:50:52,240
- 1,000 yards and closing fast!
- Conn/Radio:

734
00:50:52,320 --> 00:50:55,520
Receiving emergency action message.
Recommend alert one!

735
00:50:55,600 --> 00:50:58,960
- [Beeping]
- [Rivetti] 950 yards!

736
00:50:59,000 --> 00:51:02,120
Launch a five-inch evasion device.
Launch the countermeasures.

737
00:51:06,240 --> 00:51:08,600
- Countermeasures away, sir.
- Shift your rudder to left full.

738
00:51:08,640 --> 00:51:10,600
[Rivetti] 500 yards and closing fast.

739
00:51:16,360 --> 00:51:19,520
300 yards and closing, sir.

740
00:51:28,640 --> 00:51:31,040
Sir, the first torpedo's going
after the countermeasures!

741
00:51:33,120 --> 00:51:35,720
They missed!
They missed!

742
00:51:35,800 --> 00:51:39,480
Sonar/Conn, Conn/Sonar: Second torpedo
incoming! It's gonna be close!

743
00:51:54,640 --> 00:51:57,920
Conn/Sonar: The Akula's
disappeared in the thermal, sir.

744
00:51:58,000 --> 00:52:00,320
All ahead standard!
Rudder amid ships!

745
00:52:00,400 --> 00:52:02,800
- All ahead standard.
Rudder amid ships. Aye.
- All stations.

746
00:52:04,080 --> 00:52:06,560
All stations, report damage.
Report damage.

747
00:52:06,640 --> 00:52:10,160
[P.A.] Engine room reports
number one ASW pump failed.

748
00:52:10,240 --> 00:52:13,120
Control/Torpedo Room:
Three feet of water in the bilge.

749
00:52:13,200 --> 00:52:15,200
Request a team
with a submersible pump.

750
00:52:15,280 --> 00:52:17,760
Control/Engine Room:
Request all E-division personnel...

751
00:52:17,840 --> 00:52:20,160
lay to the engine room
to assist in ground isolation.

752
00:52:20,240 --> 00:52:22,600
Sonar/Conn:
Report hostile contact.

753
00:52:22,680 --> 00:52:26,360
- Conn/Sonar: Uh, we lost him, sir.
- Well, keep looking.

754
00:52:26,400 --> 00:52:29,000
- He's out there looking for us.
- Aye, sir.

755
00:52:29,080 --> 00:52:31,360
Weapons/Conn:
Estimated time to 1Sq.

756
00:52:31,440 --> 00:52:33,800
Conn/Weapons: Missile systems
ready to launch...

757
00:52:33,880 --> 00:52:35,880
- in six minutes.
- [Ramsey] Very well.

758
00:52:35,960 --> 00:52:38,120
Main seawater pump
is out of commission.

759
00:52:38,400 --> 00:52:40,880
Mr. Zimmer,
where's that EAM?

760
00:52:40,880 --> 00:52:41,360
Mr. Zimmer,
where's that EAM?

761
00:52:41,440 --> 00:52:43,800
- You all right, son?
- Yes, sir.

762
00:52:46,400 --> 00:52:48,440
- That's it?
- Ah, uh-huh. It's incomplete, sir.

763
00:52:48,520 --> 00:52:51,920
We lost it when the radio buoy cable
got severed.

764
00:52:52,000 --> 00:52:54,320
All right.

765
00:53:01,960 --> 00:53:04,760
All right, gentlemen,
let's get on with it.

766
00:53:04,840 --> 00:53:07,320
All ahead one-third.

767
00:53:07,400 --> 00:53:10,040
- [Bell Ringing]
- Steady as you go.

768
00:53:10,120 --> 00:53:12,920
All ahead one-third.
Steady. Aye, sir.

769
00:53:13,000 --> 00:53:16,440
Make your depth 150 feet.
Zero bubble.

770
00:53:16,520 --> 00:53:18,360
Up slow and silent
to launch depth.

771
00:53:18,440 --> 00:53:21,080
Up slow and silent to launch depth.
Aye, aye, Captain.

772
00:53:23,960 --> 00:53:27,560
Captain?
Got the EAM.

773
00:53:29,640 --> 00:53:32,320
- What do you think?
- I think there's nothing on this.

774
00:53:32,400 --> 00:53:35,600
Yes, sir. It, uh, got cut off
during the attack.

775
00:53:35,640 --> 00:53:37,680
Then it's meaningless.

776
00:53:37,720 --> 00:53:40,160
Sir, this is an EAM
pertaining to nuclear missiles.

777
00:53:40,240 --> 00:53:43,360
No, Mr. Hunter,
that's a message fragment.

778
00:53:43,440 --> 00:53:45,680
Because it got cut off
during the attack, sir.

779
00:53:45,720 --> 00:53:47,800
The message could mean anything.
It could be a message to abort.

780
00:53:47,880 --> 00:53:49,840
- It could be a message...
- Could be a fake Russian transmission.

781
00:53:49,880 --> 00:53:51,920
Which is exactly why
we need to confirm it, sir.

782
00:53:51,960 --> 00:53:54,640
- All I'm asking for is the time
we need to get back on line.
- Calm down, Mr. Hunter.

783
00:53:54,680 --> 00:53:57,040
- I am calm.
- You don't appear to be calm.

784
00:53:57,080 --> 00:54:00,400
Conn/Weapons: Missile systems
ready to launch in four minutes.

785
00:54:00,440 --> 00:54:02,320
- Step aside, seaman.
- Yes, sir.

786
00:54:02,360 --> 00:54:07,440
[Faint Radio Transmission]

787
00:54:07,480 --> 00:54:11,600
We have orders in hand, and those orders
are to make a preemptive launch.

788
00:54:11,640 --> 00:54:13,840
Every second that we lose
increases the chances...

789
00:54:13,880 --> 00:54:16,400
that by the time our missiles arrive,
their silos could be empty...

790
00:54:16,440 --> 00:54:18,440
'cause they've flown their birds
and struck us first.

791
00:54:18,520 --> 00:54:20,680
- Yes, sir.
- You know as well as I do...

792
00:54:20,760 --> 00:54:23,400
that any launch order received without
authentication is no order at all.

793
00:54:23,480 --> 00:54:25,320
- Captain... National Mili...
- That's our #1 rule.

794
00:54:25,400 --> 00:54:28,280
That rule is the basis for the scenario
we've trained on time and time again.

795
00:54:28,360 --> 00:54:30,920
- Yes, sir.
- It's a rule we follow
without exception.

796
00:54:31,000 --> 00:54:34,880
Captain, National Military Command
Center knows what sector we're in.

797
00:54:34,960 --> 00:54:37,760
They have satellites looking down on us
to see if our birds are aloft.

798
00:54:37,840 --> 00:54:40,640
And if they're not, then they give
our orders to somebody else.

799
00:54:40,720 --> 00:54:43,200
That's why we maintain more than one
sub. It's what they call "redundancy."

800
00:54:43,280 --> 00:54:46,720
- I know about redundancy, Mr. Hunter.
- All I'm saying...

801
00:54:54,480 --> 00:54:57,280
All I'm saying, Captain,
is that we have backup.

802
00:54:57,360 --> 00:55:01,560
Now, it's our duty not to launch
until we can confirm.

803
00:55:01,640 --> 00:55:06,240
You're presuming that we have other
submarines out there ready to launch.

804
00:55:06,320 --> 00:55:08,000
But as captain,
I must assume...

805
00:55:08,080 --> 00:55:10,720
that our submarines could have been
taken out by other Akulas.

806
00:55:10,800 --> 00:55:13,240
We can play these games
all night, Mr. Hunter...

807
00:55:13,360 --> 00:55:15,920
- but I don't have the luxury
of your presumptions.
- Sir...

808
00:55:15,960 --> 00:55:18,440
Mr. Hunter, we have rules that are not
open to interpretation...

809
00:55:18,520 --> 00:55:21,400
personal intuition, gut feelings,
hairs on the back of your neck...

810
00:55:21,480 --> 00:55:23,600
little devils or angels
sitting on your shoulders.

811
00:55:23,640 --> 00:55:25,400
- Captain...
- We're all very well aware...

812
00:55:25,440 --> 00:55:27,480
of what our orders are
and what those orders mean.

813
00:55:27,560 --> 00:55:30,520
They come down from
our Commander-in-Chief.
They contain no ambiguity.

814
00:55:30,600 --> 00:55:33,080
- Captain, sir...
- Mr. Hunter, I've made the decision.

815
00:55:33,160 --> 00:55:35,600
I'm captain of this boat.
Now shut the fuck up!

816
00:55:44,160 --> 00:55:46,200
Damn.

817
00:55:46,280 --> 00:55:48,400
Weapons/Conn:

818
00:55:48,440 --> 00:55:52,880
Shift targeting
to target package SLBM 64741/2.

819
00:55:52,920 --> 00:55:55,800
This is the captain.

820
00:56:00,200 --> 00:56:02,800
- Captain, I cannot concur.
- Repeat my command.

821
00:56:02,840 --> 00:56:06,000
Sir, we don't know what this means.
Our target package could have changed.

822
00:56:06,040 --> 00:56:08,520
You repeat this order
or I'll find somebody who will!

823
00:56:08,600 --> 00:56:12,560
- Hell no, you won't, sir.
- You're relieved of your position.

824
00:56:12,640 --> 00:56:14,880
Cob, remove Mr. Hunter
from the control room.

825
00:56:14,960 --> 00:56:17,840
- Get Lieutenant Zimmer in here now!
- No, sir, I do not concur...

826
00:56:17,880 --> 00:56:21,640
and I do not recognize your authority
to relieve me on the command
under Navy regulations.

827
00:56:21,720 --> 00:56:23,960
- Cob, arrest this man and get him out!
- Captain Ramsey...

828
00:56:24,000 --> 00:56:26,480
under operating procedures governing
the release of nuclear weapons...

829
00:56:26,520 --> 00:56:30,000
we cannot launch our missiles
unless both you and I agree!

830
00:56:30,080 --> 00:56:32,440
- Cob, what are you waiting for?
- Now this is more than formality, sir.

831
00:56:32,480 --> 00:56:35,120
This is why your command must
be repeated! It requires my assent!

832
00:56:35,160 --> 00:56:37,840
I do not give it, and, furthermore,
you continue upon this course...

833
00:56:37,880 --> 00:56:41,080
- and insist upon this launch without
confirming this message first...
- Son of a bitch.

834
00:56:41,120 --> 00:56:42,800
- I will be forced,
backed by the rules of precedents...
- Chief of the boat...

835
00:56:42,840 --> 00:56:44,720
- as captain and commanding
officer of the USS Alabama...
- authority and command...

836
00:56:44,760 --> 00:56:47,600
- regulation 08150H6...
- I order you to place
the X.O. Under arrest...

837
00:56:47,640 --> 00:56:49,200
- on the charge of mutiny!
- Of the Navy regulations...

838
00:56:49,240 --> 00:56:51,120
- to relieve you...
- I say again, I order you...

839
00:56:51,160 --> 00:56:53,040
- of command, Captain!
- To place the X.O. Under arrest...

840
00:56:53,080 --> 00:56:56,280
on the charge of mutiny!

841
00:56:56,320 --> 00:56:59,480
- Cob!
- Captain, please, the X.O. Is right.

842
00:56:59,520 --> 00:57:02,600
We can't launch
unless he concurs.

843
00:57:02,680 --> 00:57:05,840
"To the USS Alabama.

844
00:57:05,880 --> 00:57:07,880
Rebel-controlled missiles
being fueled.

845
00:57:07,960 --> 00:57:11,640
Launch codes compromised.
Dissidents threaten launch
at continental United States.

846
00:57:11,680 --> 00:57:15,360
Set DEFCON two.
Immediately launch ten
Trident missile sorties."

847
00:57:15,440 --> 00:57:18,680
They're fueling their missiles!
We don't have time to fuck around!

848
00:57:18,720 --> 00:57:20,920
Sir, I think you need time
to think this over.

849
00:57:20,960 --> 00:57:23,360
I don't have
to think this over!

850
00:57:25,200 --> 00:57:28,160
Captain, I relieve you
of your command of this ship.

851
00:57:28,240 --> 00:57:30,280
Cob, escort the captain
to his stateroom.

852
00:57:30,360 --> 00:57:32,720
- I'm assuming command.
- You're not assuming anything.

853
00:57:32,760 --> 00:57:37,640
Chief of the boat, Captain Ramsey's
under arrest. Lock him in his stateroom.

854
00:57:37,720 --> 00:57:40,240
- Captain, please...
- Now, Cob!

855
00:57:40,280 --> 00:57:42,800
Aye, sir.
Mitchell! Walker!

856
00:57:42,840 --> 00:57:45,240
Take the captain below.

857
00:58:11,040 --> 00:58:13,120
You're way out
of your league, Hunter.

858
00:58:13,200 --> 00:58:16,560
You're not ready to make
tough decisions yet.

859
00:58:31,120 --> 00:58:33,760
What the hell
we waitin' for?

860
00:58:47,600 --> 00:58:52,640
Anybody here disagrees
with what I've done...

861
00:58:52,720 --> 00:58:58,240
then you feel free
to relieve yourself of duty now.

862
00:59:02,320 --> 00:59:04,240
Anybody?

863
00:59:13,920 --> 00:59:15,800
All right.

864
00:59:21,440 --> 00:59:23,800
- All stations.
- Aye, sir.

865
00:59:33,240 --> 00:59:37,200
This is the Executive Officer.

866
00:59:37,280 --> 00:59:39,640
I have assumed
command of this ship...

867
00:59:39,680 --> 00:59:44,080
under authority granted me
by Navy regulations.

868
00:59:44,160 --> 00:59:47,840
I have relieved Captain Ramsey of his
duties for acting in contravention...

869
00:59:47,920 --> 00:59:50,480
of the rules and regulations
regarding nuclear weapons release.

870
00:59:50,560 --> 00:59:55,280
It is my intention
to delay the missile launch...

871
00:59:55,320 --> 00:59:59,120
maintaining our current state
of readiness...

872
00:59:59,200 --> 01:00:01,600
pending confirmation
of an emergency action message...

873
01:00:01,680 --> 01:00:05,640
- that was cut off during the attack.
- [Sighs]

874
01:00:05,720 --> 01:00:08,360
Remain at battle stations missile.

875
01:00:08,440 --> 01:00:10,280
Carry on.

876
01:00:10,360 --> 01:00:12,200
[Locks Door]

877
01:00:12,280 --> 01:00:14,120
What the hell
are we doin', Fred?

878
01:00:14,200 --> 01:00:16,680
I don't know about you,
but I'm pissin' my pants.

879
01:00:16,760 --> 01:00:20,240
[Bear Softly Growls]

880
01:00:34,200 --> 01:00:36,040
Come on, boy.

881
01:00:47,120 --> 01:00:50,880
Conn/Weapons: Russians will have
missile launch capability...

882
01:00:50,960 --> 01:00:53,640
in 39 minutes.

883
01:00:53,760 --> 01:00:55,480
[Hunter] Chief of the boat.

884
01:00:58,560 --> 01:01:00,880
Sir?

885
01:01:00,960 --> 01:01:02,800
Thank you, Cob.

886
01:01:02,880 --> 01:01:06,560
"Thank you"?
Fuck you.

887
01:01:06,600 --> 01:01:10,000
Get it straight, Mr. Hunter.
I'm not on your side.

888
01:01:10,080 --> 01:01:12,040
Now you could be wrong.

889
01:01:12,120 --> 01:01:14,920
But wrong or right, the captain can't
just replace you at will.

890
01:01:15,000 --> 01:01:19,680
That was completely improper. And that's
why I did what I did, by the book.

891
01:01:19,760 --> 01:01:22,600
I thank you anyway.

892
01:01:35,800 --> 01:01:39,920
Radio/Conn: Mr. Zimmer, get
those communications back on line now.

893
01:01:41,880 --> 01:01:44,440
We're working on it, sir.
Aye, aye, Captain.

894
01:01:45,720 --> 01:01:50,120
- Are you ready?
- Uh... ready. Go.

895
01:01:50,200 --> 01:01:52,360
Jesus.
This fuckin' thing...

896
01:01:52,440 --> 01:01:55,240
You know, this whole system is crashed;
radio buoy is severed.

897
01:01:55,320 --> 01:01:58,080
- What the fuck does he want us to do?
- Shit electrons?

898
01:01:58,120 --> 01:02:00,480
Hey, Vossler, we need communications,
not smart-ass remarks.

899
01:02:00,520 --> 01:02:03,280
- Aye, sir.
- All stop, ten degrees up.

900
01:02:03,360 --> 01:02:06,400
- Ten up. Aye, sir.
- All stop. Aye, sir. Enters all stop.

901
01:02:23,560 --> 01:02:27,440
- [Bleeping]
- Conn/Sonar: Holy shit, sir!

902
01:02:27,520 --> 01:02:29,760
He's right on top of us!
He's turning toward!

903
01:02:33,280 --> 01:02:35,200
- Range?
- 600 yards!

904
01:02:38,080 --> 01:02:42,400
Conn/Sonar: Torpedoes in the water!
Bearing 048, 050!

905
01:02:44,480 --> 01:02:46,400
- Left full rudder!
- Left full rudder! Aye, sir!

906
01:02:46,480 --> 01:02:49,400
All ahead full!
Zero bubble!

907
01:02:49,440 --> 01:02:51,360
Sir, don't you want to fire back?
Torpedoes are ready, sir.

908
01:02:51,400 --> 01:02:53,280
No, we're in too close.
Our weapons won't have time to arm.

909
01:02:53,320 --> 01:02:56,320
All ahead flank! Chief of the watch
to maneuvering. Give me max speed now!

910
01:02:56,400 --> 01:02:58,720
- [Bell Ringing]
- Maximum speed! Aye, sir!

911
01:03:03,520 --> 01:03:07,360
Sonar/Conn: Let me know when our range
to that Akula is open to 1,000 yards!

912
01:03:07,440 --> 01:03:10,000
- Conn/Sonar: Aye, sir!
- Damn it! Let's just shoot this fucker!

913
01:03:10,080 --> 01:03:13,160
- What's 1,000 yards for?
- 'Cause it takes 1,000 yards
for the torpedoes to arm!

914
01:03:13,240 --> 01:03:15,080
Jesus! Who'd you fuck
to get on this ship?

915
01:03:16,640 --> 01:03:19,040
- [Bleeping]
- Conn/Sonar:

916
01:03:19,120 --> 01:03:22,840
Torpedoes 150 yards
and closing fast, sir!

917
01:03:22,880 --> 01:03:26,280
Bearing 070, 074!

918
01:03:27,840 --> 01:03:29,880
Launch port countermeasures!

919
01:03:32,360 --> 01:03:34,360
- Countermeasures away, sir!
- Rig ship for impact.

920
01:03:34,400 --> 01:03:36,880
Rig ship for impact!
Aye, sir!

921
01:03:48,320 --> 01:03:50,840
They missed! They missed!
They passed astern!

922
01:03:50,920 --> 01:03:55,960
They were too close to arm, sir.
Conn/Sonar: Range to the Akula:
950 yards and opening fast!

923
01:03:56,040 --> 01:03:58,280
Go to manual on the arming mechanisms,
tubes two and four.

924
01:04:01,200 --> 01:04:04,200
- Snapshot, two and four.
- Snapshot, two and four.
Tubes fired electrically, sir.

925
01:04:13,600 --> 01:04:16,120
Sonar/Conn: Give me exact ranging
and speed on our weapons.

926
01:04:16,160 --> 01:04:19,760
Range: 300 yards
at 50 knots, sir!

927
01:04:22,280 --> 01:04:24,800
200 yards, 50 knots!

928
01:04:27,200 --> 01:04:30,200
- 100 yards, 55 knots!
- [Bleeping]

929
01:04:30,240 --> 01:04:32,640
75 yards!
Weapons ready for arming, sir!

930
01:04:32,720 --> 01:04:35,080
- Steady course 231.
- Aye, sir. 231.

931
01:04:36,200 --> 01:04:40,760
Arm torpedoes
two and four... now!

932
01:04:40,840 --> 01:04:43,040
Torpedoes armed, sir!

933
01:04:44,480 --> 01:04:47,400
- [Beeping]
- We're locked on the Akula!

934
01:05:00,040 --> 01:05:03,480
- You got him, sir! You got him!
- [All Cheering]

935
01:05:03,560 --> 01:05:06,680
- [Cheering Continues]
- [Bear Barks]

936
01:05:06,720 --> 01:05:09,280
[Cheering Continues]

937
01:05:11,120 --> 01:05:15,120
Conn/Sonar: Incoming torpedo! They got
it off before they got hit, sir!

938
01:05:15,200 --> 01:05:17,120
Right full rudder!
Launch starboard countermeasures!

939
01:05:18,720 --> 01:05:21,080
- Countermeasures away, sir!
- Dive! Make your depth 1,200 feet!

940
01:05:21,120 --> 01:05:23,040
[Cob] Point it down now!
Take her deep! Take her deep!

941
01:05:23,080 --> 01:05:25,160
Full dive on those planes!
Let's go, let's go, let's go!

942
01:05:27,520 --> 01:05:31,480
- Hang on, everybody!
- [Sonar Bleeping]

943
01:05:48,240 --> 01:05:50,160
[Yelling]

944
01:05:50,240 --> 01:05:53,080
[Bear Barking, Growling]

945
01:05:53,120 --> 01:05:57,560
[Continues Barking, Growling]

946
01:05:57,640 --> 01:06:00,280
Is everybody okay?

947
01:06:00,360 --> 01:06:02,240
Yeah!

948
01:06:07,680 --> 01:06:11,240
Open aft main drain suction!

949
01:06:11,320 --> 01:06:14,280
Start the drain pump!
Go, go, go!

950
01:06:17,920 --> 01:06:20,080
All stations,
make damage report to Control.

951
01:06:20,160 --> 01:06:22,760
Control, this is Bilge Bay!

952
01:06:22,840 --> 01:06:24,760
We've got out-of-control flooding!

953
01:06:24,800 --> 01:06:27,640
- [Shouting]
- Request damage control!

954
01:06:27,680 --> 01:06:30,360
- Mr. Mahoney, get a damage control
party down there!
- Aye, sir!

955
01:06:30,440 --> 01:06:33,000
Forward damage control party,
get Lieutenant Hellerman!

956
01:06:33,080 --> 01:06:35,040
Flooding in the bilge bay!
Get him down there now!

957
01:06:40,080 --> 01:06:42,800
Conn/Maneuvering:
We've lost propulsion, sir!

958
01:06:42,880 --> 01:06:46,080
- Chief of the boat, how we doin'?
- Sir, we are going down!

959
01:06:46,120 --> 01:06:49,680
- I need propulsion!
- Forward ballast tanks are damaged, sir!

960
01:06:49,760 --> 01:06:54,400
- Forward air pressure: Zero!
- Maneuvering/Conn:
Restore propulsion as soon as possible.

961
01:06:54,480 --> 01:06:57,880
Conn/Maneuvering: Restoring propulsion
as soon as possible! Aye, sir!

962
01:06:57,960 --> 01:07:03,040
[Hull Groaning]

963
01:07:10,960 --> 01:07:13,400
Control/Bilge Bay:
Flooding is slowed!

964
01:07:13,440 --> 01:07:15,960
I think we got it
under control, sir!

965
01:07:16,000 --> 01:07:20,280
Passing 1,500 feet.
At 1,850 it's all over.

966
01:07:29,280 --> 01:07:32,680
[Hull Groaning]

967
01:07:35,360 --> 01:07:37,680
[Cob] Passing 1,600 feet.

968
01:07:49,280 --> 01:07:52,280
Barnes, get over here!
Help me with this loose valve!

969
01:08:04,480 --> 01:08:07,640
[Cob] Passing 1,650 feet.

970
01:08:07,720 --> 01:08:12,960
[Hull Groaning]

971
01:08:13,040 --> 01:08:16,080
[Submarine Shaking]

972
01:08:16,160 --> 01:08:18,880
- What the fuck is going on?
- [Rivetti] Take it easy.

973
01:08:30,640 --> 01:08:33,600
Conn/Bilge Bay:
Flooding has recommenced!

974
01:08:33,680 --> 01:08:35,840
It looks like three men are trapped!

975
01:08:35,960 --> 01:08:40,000
Bilge Bay/Conn: Try and get those men
out of there and seal that bay.

976
01:08:40,080 --> 01:08:42,400
Sir, if we don't seal the bilge bay now,
we'll lose the ship!

977
01:08:42,440 --> 01:08:44,920
[Hull Groaning]

978
01:08:45,000 --> 01:08:48,360
Bilge Bay/Conn:
Can you get the men out?

979
01:08:48,440 --> 01:08:51,280
Sir, there's no fuckin' way!
If I go down there, I'll never get out!

980
01:08:53,320 --> 01:08:55,280
Barnes, come on!
You've got to come!

981
01:08:55,360 --> 01:09:00,000
Move, move! Barnes, come on, come on!
You can do it! Move it!

982
01:09:00,080 --> 01:09:02,720
Bilge Bay/Conn:
Seal that bay.

983
01:09:02,760 --> 01:09:05,440
Barnes, let's go! Come on!
I've got to close the hatch!

984
01:09:07,560 --> 01:09:10,760
What the fuck
are we doing here?

985
01:09:10,840 --> 01:09:13,400
Bilge Bay/Conn:
I say again, seal that bay.

986
01:09:13,480 --> 01:09:16,040
Sir, there are men down there,
and they're gonna drown!

987
01:09:16,120 --> 01:09:18,680
Lieutenant Hellerman,
you have your orders!

988
01:09:18,760 --> 01:09:21,600
Now seal the goddamn bay
before we all go down!

989
01:09:21,640 --> 01:09:25,280
Barnes!
Please get the fuck out!

990
01:09:29,040 --> 01:09:31,080
Barnes!

991
01:09:34,560 --> 01:09:38,360
Come on!
Barnes!

992
01:10:09,960 --> 01:10:12,880
Conn/Bilge Bay:

993
01:10:12,960 --> 01:10:16,240
Seawater hatch is sealed, sir!

994
01:10:21,440 --> 01:10:23,600
Very well.

995
01:10:31,560 --> 01:10:34,400
[Cob] Passing 1,800 feet.

996
01:10:34,440 --> 01:10:37,200
Approaching hull crush depth, sir.

997
01:10:58,640 --> 01:11:01,080
1825.

998
01:11:01,160 --> 01:11:03,360
Conn/Maneuvering:
Turbine power restored!

999
01:11:03,400 --> 01:11:06,320
Main seawater cross valve repaired!

1000
01:11:12,760 --> 01:11:16,960
- And rising.
- Propulsion limit! Ahead full, sir!

1001
01:11:17,040 --> 01:11:19,200
- Take us up to periscope depth.
- Aye, aye, sir.

1002
01:11:38,880 --> 01:11:40,760
Give me five.

1003
01:11:46,160 --> 01:11:48,520
[Sobbing]

1004
01:11:48,600 --> 01:11:51,960
All right, we're livin'.
We're livin', gentlemen.

1005
01:12:04,960 --> 01:12:07,960
- Step aside, Tommy.
- I'm sorry, sir. The X.O. Ordered...

1006
01:12:08,000 --> 01:12:10,360
Fuck the X.O.!

1007
01:12:10,400 --> 01:12:14,480
This ship has been hit,
and I'm going in to see my captain.

1008
01:12:14,560 --> 01:12:16,400
Now stand aside.

1009
01:12:16,480 --> 01:12:18,960
Stand aside!

1010
01:12:20,800 --> 01:12:23,400
[Unlocking Door, Knocking]
Captain?

1011
01:12:23,480 --> 01:12:28,120
[Opera Playing]

1012
01:12:28,160 --> 01:12:31,120
- Sir.
- How bad is it, Mr. Dougherty?

1013
01:12:31,200 --> 01:12:36,520
- It's bad, sir.
- I've just been looking
at Hunter's file here.

1014
01:12:36,600 --> 01:12:39,600
The closest to combat he's been
is a policy seminar.

1015
01:12:39,680 --> 01:12:42,600
Give me an order, sir.

1016
01:12:42,680 --> 01:12:47,360
As quietly as you can, you get
to Mr. Zimmer and Mr. Westergaurd.

1017
01:12:47,440 --> 01:12:49,480
How about Linkletter?

1018
01:12:49,560 --> 01:12:53,160
Nah, you won't be able to talk
to the TSO. He's at the conn.

1019
01:12:53,240 --> 01:12:56,320
But you can get to Weps.
We got to have Weps. He's the key.

1020
01:12:56,400 --> 01:13:01,120
You get me those men, a small security
force; then come back and get me.

1021
01:13:01,160 --> 01:13:02,280
Aye, sir.

1022
01:13:02,360 --> 01:13:03,840
Don't get overzealous and
try to recruit the whole ship.

1023
01:13:03,920 --> 01:13:06,240
We'll lead from the top down.

1024
01:13:06,280 --> 01:13:09,240
Aye, sir. Right away.

1025
01:13:09,320 --> 01:13:11,880
[Opera Continues]

1026
01:13:11,960 --> 01:13:13,800
[Door Closes]

1027
01:13:15,560 --> 01:13:17,480
The radio's 50%.

1028
01:13:19,800 --> 01:13:22,120
Can I talk to you
in the passageway?

1029
01:13:22,200 --> 01:13:25,840
Right now, Pete.
Come on.

1030
01:13:38,240 --> 01:13:40,640
[Sighs]
What's goin' on?

1031
01:13:40,680 --> 01:13:43,240
We're not gonna let this go down
with the X.O. At the helm.

1032
01:13:43,320 --> 01:13:45,800
- We're not?
- No, we're not. I've been
with the captain for years...

1033
01:13:45,880 --> 01:13:49,120
and this asshole Hunter
shows up, and I'm supposed
to follow him 'cause he says so?

1034
01:13:49,160 --> 01:13:51,640
You're not supposed to;
you've been ordered to.

1035
01:13:51,680 --> 01:13:53,720
That's what this is about:
Proper orders.

1036
01:13:53,800 --> 01:13:56,480
Proper orders? He has proper orders.
He won't act on them.

1037
01:13:56,560 --> 01:13:58,840
He's in command now!

1038
01:13:58,880 --> 01:14:03,000
If they order him to launch, we'll
launch, and we'll blow 'em all to hell.

1039
01:14:03,040 --> 01:14:06,280
But I'd rather go down myself
than get this one wrong.

1040
01:14:06,360 --> 01:14:08,200
Look, our procedures are clear.

1041
01:14:08,280 --> 01:14:11,320
In the absence of a contravening order,
in a situation like this...

1042
01:14:11,360 --> 01:14:13,880
- we follow the orders in hand.
- Exactly.

1043
01:14:13,920 --> 01:14:16,040
You know how many checks we do to make
sure a launch order is authentic?

1044
01:14:16,120 --> 01:14:18,680
The X.O. Agreed
with those orders.

1045
01:14:18,720 --> 01:14:20,920
Now he just wants to throw them away?
They don't count?

1046
01:14:20,960 --> 01:14:24,960
- He's lost his nerve.
- Bullshit! I know this guy, Bobby!

1047
01:14:25,040 --> 01:14:26,880
Weps, we've been ordered to launch.

1048
01:14:26,960 --> 01:14:29,440
Now why in the world would we do that if
they weren't prepared to launch at us?

1049
01:14:29,520 --> 01:14:32,680
We don't know that for sure.
That's the whole point.

1050
01:14:32,760 --> 01:14:34,920
That's why he wants time
to confirm the message.

1051
01:14:35,000 --> 01:14:37,800
That's the whole fucking point is
we don't have time!

1052
01:14:37,880 --> 01:14:41,000
Radchenko is fueling his birds.
Now why do you think he's doing that?

1053
01:14:41,080 --> 01:14:46,240
Why? You don't put on a condom
unless you gonna fuck!

1054
01:14:46,280 --> 01:14:49,440
Go back to your station.
Go back to your station and stay there.

1055
01:14:52,280 --> 01:14:54,120
Come on, man.

1056
01:14:55,160 --> 01:14:58,760
Peter, think about your family, man.

1057
01:14:58,840 --> 01:15:02,680
I am. I am!

1058
01:15:08,280 --> 01:15:11,160
I mean, what do you...
What do you plan to do?

1059
01:15:11,200 --> 01:15:16,120
Nothing without you.
You're senior officer department head.
The TSO's with Hunter.

1060
01:15:16,200 --> 01:15:18,280
And you have the keys
to the small arms locker.

1061
01:15:18,360 --> 01:15:22,840
Now we want to recruit a few more men,
and then we're gonna open that arsenal.

1062
01:15:22,880 --> 01:15:24,760
[Dougherty] I just talked
to the captain in his room.

1063
01:15:24,800 --> 01:15:27,080
He specifically asked for you.

1064
01:15:27,160 --> 01:15:29,640
He says we cannot go
without you.

1065
01:15:29,720 --> 01:15:34,600
I don't believe this.
[Sighs]

1066
01:15:34,680 --> 01:15:36,760
This is a mutiny, Peter.

1067
01:15:36,840 --> 01:15:38,720
There's only two sides
to a mutiny.

1068
01:15:38,760 --> 01:15:41,240
Now, your captain
is asking for your help.

1069
01:15:41,280 --> 01:15:44,840
What are you gonna do?

1070
01:15:45,880 --> 01:15:48,280
What are you gonna do?

1071
01:15:59,560 --> 01:16:01,440
All right.

1072
01:16:03,840 --> 01:16:07,800
Conn/Weapons: Russian missiles
will have launch capability...

1073
01:16:07,840 --> 01:16:09,800
in 24 minutes.

1074
01:16:24,960 --> 01:16:27,240
You're doing the right thing.

1075
01:16:36,440 --> 01:16:41,440
[Booming, Electricity Buzzing]

1076
01:16:41,480 --> 01:16:43,520
[Mahoney]
Electrical power has been restored.

1077
01:16:43,560 --> 01:16:46,720
- [Growling]
- All stations, prepare to
reinitiate the system.

1078
01:16:46,760 --> 01:16:48,800
[Continues Growling]

1079
01:16:51,880 --> 01:16:55,600
Radio/Conn: Mr. Zimmer, what's the
status on that radio repair?

1080
01:16:55,680 --> 01:16:58,920
Conn/Radio: All systems are still
down, sir. Lieutenant Zimmer isn't here.

1081
01:16:58,960 --> 01:17:01,640
- Where is he?
- [Vossler] I don't know, sir.

1082
01:17:03,200 --> 01:17:05,120
Very well.

1083
01:17:09,400 --> 01:17:12,040
- Mr. Mahoney has the conn.
- Aye, sir. I have the conn.

1084
01:17:12,120 --> 01:17:13,960
- Cob.
- Sir?

1085
01:17:14,040 --> 01:17:16,320
- Send a man and find Zimmer.
- Aye, sir.

1086
01:17:16,360 --> 01:17:19,520
- Get a side arm.
- Aye, aye, sir.

1087
01:17:19,560 --> 01:17:21,600
- Chief Young.
- Aye, Chief.

1088
01:17:23,240 --> 01:17:25,880
Turn around!
Move it!

1089
01:17:25,960 --> 01:17:28,480
- [Growling]
- At ease, sailor.

1090
01:17:32,680 --> 01:17:34,920
[Bear Growling]

1091
01:17:35,000 --> 01:17:37,440
- [Bear Barks]
- Sir.

1092
01:17:37,480 --> 01:17:39,400
- Thank you, Mr. Ince.
- [Growling]

1093
01:17:39,440 --> 01:17:41,320
- Mr. Westergaurd.
- Sir.

1094
01:17:41,400 --> 01:17:44,240
- Mr. Zimmer.
- [Zimmer] Ready, sir.

1095
01:17:44,320 --> 01:17:47,640
Let's get on with it.

1096
01:17:48,760 --> 01:17:51,680
- [Barking]
- [Weps] Stand guard.

1097
01:17:55,880 --> 01:17:59,160
All you people,
return to your stations!

1098
01:17:59,240 --> 01:18:01,120
- Mr. Rivetti.
- Sir?

1099
01:18:01,160 --> 01:18:03,520
- Follow me, please.
- Yes, sir.

1100
01:18:12,680 --> 01:18:15,360
[Man Cocks Pistol]

1101
01:18:17,640 --> 01:18:20,080
Is there a problem, sir?

1102
01:18:23,840 --> 01:18:26,320
These are the keys
to the entire submarine.

1103
01:18:34,600 --> 01:18:37,440
Conn/Weapons:
Russian missiles...

1104
01:18:37,520 --> 01:18:39,560
will have launch capability
in 21 minutes.

1105
01:18:39,720 --> 01:18:41,680
Who's in charge here?

1106
01:18:41,760 --> 01:18:43,600
Shit!

1107
01:18:43,680 --> 01:18:46,160
Me, sir. Oh, fuck.

1108
01:18:47,480 --> 01:18:50,640
- How long is it gonna take?
- I don't know, sir.

1109
01:18:50,720 --> 01:18:52,880
- Do you know what's going on here?
- Yes, sir.

1110
01:18:52,960 --> 01:18:55,720
No, I don't think you do.
Let me explain it to you.

1111
01:18:55,760 --> 01:18:58,800
If we launch and we're wrong...

1112
01:18:58,880 --> 01:19:01,000
what's left of Russia
is gonna launch at us.

1113
01:19:01,040 --> 01:19:03,120
There will be a nuclear holocaust
beyond imagination.

1114
01:19:03,200 --> 01:19:06,320
So it's all about knowing,
Mr. Vossler.

1115
01:19:06,400 --> 01:19:08,880
We have to know whether or not our order
to launch has been recalled or not.

1116
01:19:08,960 --> 01:19:12,240
The only way we're gonna know is if
you fix that radio. You understand me?

1117
01:19:12,320 --> 01:19:14,200
Yes, sir.

1118
01:19:14,280 --> 01:19:17,000
You ever watch Star Trek?

1119
01:19:17,080 --> 01:19:20,960
- Yeah, I seen Star Trek.
- Star Trek. You know, Star Trek.
The USS Enterprise. All right.

1120
01:19:21,040 --> 01:19:22,920
You remember when the Klingons
were gonna blow up the Enterprise?

1121
01:19:22,960 --> 01:19:25,720
And Captain Kirk calls down to Scotty,
"Scotty, I gotta have more power."

1122
01:19:25,800 --> 01:19:29,040
- He needs more, more warp speed. Yeah.
- Warp speed. Exactly.

1123
01:19:29,120 --> 01:19:31,520
Well, I'm Captain Kirk.
You're Scotty. I need more power.

1124
01:19:31,600 --> 01:19:34,280
If you do not get this radio up,
a billion people are gonna die.

1125
01:19:34,320 --> 01:19:37,280
It's up to you. I know that's a shitty
deal, but you got it. Can you handle it?

1126
01:19:40,320 --> 01:19:43,200
Scotty?

1127
01:19:44,720 --> 01:19:46,600
Aye, Captain.

1128
01:19:47,720 --> 01:19:50,080
You got anything?

1129
01:19:50,160 --> 01:19:52,480
- No, Vossler.
- Then get on it.

1130
01:19:59,640 --> 01:20:02,280
- I have the conn.
- [Mahoney] X.O. Has the conn.

1131
01:20:02,320 --> 01:20:04,680
Chief of the boat,
make your depth 75 feet.

1132
01:20:04,720 --> 01:20:06,640
Continue up
to periscope depth.

1133
01:20:06,720 --> 01:20:11,160
- Belay that order!
- [Pistols Cocking]

1134
01:20:21,240 --> 01:20:26,920
Any officers or chiefs feel you've been
unjustly caught up in this thing...

1135
01:20:26,960 --> 01:20:30,080
you stand with me now.

1136
01:21:00,880 --> 01:21:02,840
[Sighs]

1137
01:21:06,440 --> 01:21:09,240
Sir, propulsion
has been restored.

1138
01:21:09,320 --> 01:21:12,040
All flooding
has been contained.

1139
01:21:12,080 --> 01:21:15,800
All communications
are still down.

1140
01:21:21,360 --> 01:21:23,400
Take him away.

1141
01:21:23,480 --> 01:21:25,360
Lock him up
in the officers' mess.

1142
01:21:59,560 --> 01:22:02,320
Of all the people.

1143
01:22:12,360 --> 01:22:17,200
Weps, return to missile control.
Mr. Zimmer, you stay with me.

1144
01:22:17,280 --> 01:22:19,120
- Aye, aye, sir.
- The rest of you,
return to your stations.

1145
01:22:19,200 --> 01:22:22,560
Inform your men directly
that the captain is in command.

1146
01:22:22,600 --> 01:22:25,000
- I have the conn.
- Captain has the conn.

1147
01:22:25,080 --> 01:22:27,880
Diving officer,
make your depth 150 feet.

1148
01:22:27,960 --> 01:22:30,880
- At 150 feet. Aye, sir.
- 1MC.

1149
01:22:30,920 --> 01:22:32,800
[Radioman] Aye, sir.

1150
01:22:32,840 --> 01:22:35,040
May I have
your attention, please.

1151
01:22:35,080 --> 01:22:37,920
Crew of the USS Alabama...

1152
01:22:37,960 --> 01:22:41,280
attempted mutiny has been put down.

1153
01:22:41,360 --> 01:22:44,480
We'll maintain security alert.

1154
01:22:44,520 --> 01:22:47,840
Authorized movement
only in two-man teams.

1155
01:22:47,880 --> 01:22:50,240
In the absence
of further radio communication...

1156
01:22:50,280 --> 01:22:52,640
on orders from
the National Command Center...

1157
01:22:52,680 --> 01:22:55,680
we'll achieve launch depth
