1173
01:23:44,360 --> 01:23:46,280
This is the X.O.

1174
01:23:46,320 --> 01:23:49,040
Weapons/Conn:

1175
01:23:49,120 --> 01:23:54,200
Confirm target package
SLBM 64741/2...

1176
01:23:54,280 --> 01:23:57,040
for missiles 1 - 5
and 20 - 24.

1177
01:23:57,120 --> 01:23:59,920
- Target package confirmation, sir.
- This is the captain.

1178
01:24:08,240 --> 01:24:10,120
Conn/Weapons:

1179
01:24:10,160 --> 01:24:14,720
Confirm target package
SLBM 64741/2...

1180
01:24:14,760 --> 01:24:16,800
for missiles 1 - 5
and 20 - 24.

1181
01:24:16,840 --> 01:24:18,720
Aye, sir.

1182
01:24:27,720 --> 01:24:30,200
Look, it's not a mutiny.
I did everything by the book.

1183
01:24:30,240 --> 01:24:32,680
It's not about the book.

1184
01:24:32,760 --> 01:24:37,720
If the Russians are gonna launch
and we do nothing, who's gonna stop 'em?

1185
01:24:37,760 --> 01:24:42,000
Half of me is glad the captain
came back. He could be right, you know.

1186
01:24:42,080 --> 01:24:45,080
No orders are valid, Cob,
if they're wrong.

1187
01:24:45,160 --> 01:24:48,200
- We don't know if they're wrong.
- That's true. We don't know.

1188
01:24:48,280 --> 01:24:50,200
That's why we have
to find out first.

1189
01:24:57,240 --> 01:25:00,800
What if Radchenko surrendered
and it's over? Hmm?

1190
01:25:00,880 --> 01:25:03,280
We launch. They see us.

1191
01:25:03,360 --> 01:25:05,920
They launch.

1192
01:25:05,960 --> 01:25:09,200
Our birds pass each other
in the air. Boom!

1193
01:25:09,280 --> 01:25:11,880
- What do you got?
- Nuclear war.

1194
01:25:11,960 --> 01:25:14,280
Nuclear holocaust.

1195
01:25:19,400 --> 01:25:22,840
- What are you doing down here?
- Jesus, I was just going to the bath...

1196
01:25:22,920 --> 01:25:24,840
Rivetti, nobody moves alone!
Come on. You know the drill.

1197
01:25:24,920 --> 01:25:27,560
- What, Bennefield, I need
an escort to take a shit?
- Shut up!

1198
01:25:27,640 --> 01:25:31,120
Now I'm gonna call Control.
You stay right there.

1199
01:25:31,200 --> 01:25:33,120
- Fuck that.
- I mean it, man.

1200
01:25:37,400 --> 01:25:40,200
Okay, Moebius,
open the door.

1201
01:25:40,280 --> 01:25:43,080
- You broke my nose, man.
- Shut up, fat boy.

1202
01:25:46,280 --> 01:25:49,440
- Mr. Rivetti, I'm impressed.
- I never liked him, sir.

1203
01:25:49,480 --> 01:25:52,760
Rivetti, go to laundry. Get four sets
of coveralls and four caps.

1204
01:25:52,800 --> 01:25:55,520
- [Rivetti] Aye, sir.
- Just relax.

1205
01:25:59,720 --> 01:26:02,560
Davis. Can I talk
to you a second?

1206
01:26:02,600 --> 01:26:04,560
Come on.

1207
01:26:06,760 --> 01:26:09,240
- Everybody ready?
- Let's do it.

1208
01:26:18,560 --> 01:26:22,040
- We're with you, sir.
- Let's go.

1209
01:26:31,200 --> 01:26:34,480
- Approaching launch depth.
- Very well.

1210
01:26:34,560 --> 01:26:36,880
Make your depth 150 feet.

1211
01:26:36,960 --> 01:26:39,320
Zero bubble.
Commence hovering.

1212
01:26:39,400 --> 01:26:41,280
Zero bubble.
Commence hovering. Aye, sir.

1213
01:26:41,320 --> 01:26:44,080
Conn/Weapons: Estimated time
to weapons system 1Sq:

1214
01:26:44,160 --> 01:26:47,400
Three minutes,
30 seconds, sir.

1215
01:26:47,480 --> 01:26:51,680
Conn/Weapons: Russian missiles will have
launch capability in 12 minutes.

1216
01:26:51,720 --> 01:26:53,600
Opening missile hatches.

1217
01:27:08,360 --> 01:27:10,240
[Phone Rings]

1218
01:27:10,280 --> 01:27:14,000
- Weps.
- Weps, this is Hunter. Listen to me.

1219
01:27:14,080 --> 01:27:16,720
- Where are you?
- Don't worry about where I am.

1220
01:27:16,800 --> 01:27:19,720
You cannot proceed. We got other ships
out there that can handle this.

1221
01:27:19,800 --> 01:27:22,680
You can't be influenced by the captain
or anybody else. Make up your own mind.

1222
01:27:22,720 --> 01:27:25,240
- [Clock Beeps]
- Conn/Weapons:

1223
01:27:25,320 --> 01:27:28,080
Estimated time to missile launch:
Three minutes and counting, sir.

1224
01:27:28,160 --> 01:27:30,480
Weps, Weps, listen.
Don't do this.

1225
01:27:30,560 --> 01:27:32,400
Don't do this.
Once you launch, they cannot come back.

1226
01:27:32,480 --> 01:27:35,280
They cannot come back, Weps.
And you know the repercussions
if we're wrong, goddamn it!

1227
01:27:35,360 --> 01:27:40,720
Weps, if we fire now, we'll be firing
while we're blind and crippled.
You understand me?

1228
01:27:40,800 --> 01:27:44,080
- Where the fuck are you?
- Do not remove that firing trigger!

1229
01:27:44,160 --> 01:27:46,640
Do not open the safe, Weps!
It's up to you!

1230
01:27:46,720 --> 01:27:49,520
You're the only one that knows
the combination! It's up to you, Weps!

1231
01:27:49,600 --> 01:27:51,600
It's up to you.

1232
01:27:51,680 --> 01:27:53,520
[Line Disconnects]

1233
01:27:53,600 --> 01:27:56,320
Mind your fuckin' panel!

1234
01:28:02,680 --> 01:28:05,440
- You guys ready?
- Just about, sir.

1235
01:28:05,520 --> 01:28:07,840
[Ringing Phone]

1236
01:28:07,920 --> 01:28:10,160
Radio/X. O: Vossler?

1237
01:28:10,240 --> 01:28:13,360
X.O. /Radio: Sir...

1238
01:28:13,440 --> 01:28:15,320
- I don't know, sir.
- Vossler, calm down. Just calm down.

1239
01:28:15,400 --> 01:28:18,680
- Take a deep breath. Are you calm?
- Yeah, sort of.

1240
01:28:18,720 --> 01:28:21,600
Get the radio fixed, Vossler.
I could have built one by now.
How long is it gonna take you?

1241
01:28:21,640 --> 01:28:24,160
I don't know.

1242
01:28:25,160 --> 01:28:27,520
Well, how much time
do you need?

1243
01:28:28,800 --> 01:28:30,720
[Line Disconnects]
Shit!

1244
01:28:30,800 --> 01:28:33,120
Let's go.

1245
01:28:35,880 --> 01:28:41,440
Missile tubes 1 - 5
and 20 - 24 at 1Sq, sir.

1246
01:28:41,480 --> 01:28:44,720
[Panel Beeping]

1247
01:28:44,800 --> 01:28:49,320
Ship is hovering on automatic.
Dive is at 1Sq, Captain.

1248
01:28:49,400 --> 01:28:53,880
Missiles at 1Sq.
Ready to launch, sir.

1249
01:28:53,920 --> 01:28:58,280
[Panel Beeping]

1250
01:28:58,360 --> 01:29:01,520
[Flipping Buttons]
Sir, weapons system is at 1Sq.

1251
01:29:01,600 --> 01:29:05,960
- Missiles are ready for launch, sir.
- Very well.

1252
01:29:06,040 --> 01:29:08,280
- Weapons.
- Aye, sir.

1253
01:29:08,320 --> 01:29:12,120
Weapons/Conn:
Remove the tactical firing trigger.

1254
01:29:12,160 --> 01:29:16,800
[Panel Beeping]

1255
01:29:16,840 --> 01:29:21,880
[Beeping Continues]

1256
01:29:23,360 --> 01:29:26,080
- 1MC.
- Aye, sir.

1257
01:29:26,120 --> 01:29:28,280
Weapons, this is the captain.

1258
01:29:28,320 --> 01:29:30,440
Unlock the tactical
firing trigger.

1259
01:29:30,520 --> 01:29:33,720
[Beeping Continues]

1260
01:29:33,760 --> 01:29:36,240
Weps?

1261
01:29:36,320 --> 01:29:38,880
Missiles are ready
to launch, man.

1262
01:29:38,920 --> 01:29:42,840
[Beeping Continues]

1263
01:29:42,880 --> 01:29:44,760
Sir.

1264
01:29:46,080 --> 01:29:48,680
Shit.

1265
01:29:48,760 --> 01:29:53,040
Mr. Zimmer...
no one is to touch this key.

1266
01:29:53,120 --> 01:29:55,560
I'm going to launch
from missile control.

1267
01:29:55,640 --> 01:29:58,000
- [Zimmer] Aye, aye, sir.
- Westergaurd.

1268
01:29:58,080 --> 01:29:59,720
- Sir.
- Dougherty. Come with me.

1269
01:29:59,800 --> 01:30:03,520
- Mr. Mahoney, take the conn.
- Aye, sir. I have the conn.

1270
01:30:05,480 --> 01:30:07,680
What are you doing, man?
We're at 1Sq. We're ready.

1271
01:30:07,720 --> 01:30:10,760
[Panel Beeping]

1272
01:30:10,840 --> 01:30:12,680
- Mr. Dougherty.
- Aye.

1273
01:30:12,760 --> 01:30:15,400
- Station your guards fore and aft.
- Last two, forward hatch!

1274
01:30:15,480 --> 01:30:17,880
First two, aft hatch!

1275
01:30:17,920 --> 01:30:20,760
They're gonna fire
from missile control.

1276
01:30:22,280 --> 01:30:24,440
We've got to get back to the conn
and disarm the system. Come on.

1277
01:30:24,480 --> 01:30:28,120
We'll travel
in the crawl spaces.

1278
01:30:41,280 --> 01:30:43,880
Mr. Ince!

1279
01:30:43,960 --> 01:30:47,720
Mr. Ince, remove
the tactical firing key.

1280
01:30:47,800 --> 01:30:50,160
Sir, it is my duty to...

1281
01:30:50,240 --> 01:30:53,560
Son, don't talk to me about duty.
Open the fucking safe!

1282
01:31:00,360 --> 01:31:03,600
[Panel Beeping]

1283
01:31:03,680 --> 01:31:06,240
I can't do that, sir.

1284
01:31:11,520 --> 01:31:14,080
I'm gonna count to three...

1285
01:31:14,120 --> 01:31:16,320
and then I'm gonna blow
your fucking head off.

1286
01:31:16,360 --> 01:31:18,840
One.

1287
01:31:18,880 --> 01:31:20,680
Two.

1288
01:31:24,040 --> 01:31:26,720
Shit!

1289
01:31:26,760 --> 01:31:29,680
It does me no good
to kill you.

1290
01:31:29,760 --> 01:31:32,480
You're the only one
that knows the combination.

1291
01:31:34,920 --> 01:31:37,240
However...

1292
01:31:37,280 --> 01:31:41,400
Petty Officer Hilaire
doesn't know the combination!

1293
01:31:43,680 --> 01:31:48,160
Millions of lives at stake here, Peter!
Don't make a dumb decision! One!

1294
01:31:49,800 --> 01:31:52,760
- Two!
- Sir!

1295
01:32:16,640 --> 01:32:18,640
- Cob!
- Yo.

1296
01:32:18,720 --> 01:32:21,040
You and Hunsicker are going
to enter the conn from the bow.

1297
01:32:21,120 --> 01:32:25,600
Rivetti, Linkletter and myself
will come in through the aft.
You jump right on Zimmer, okay?

1298
01:32:41,680 --> 01:32:43,760
Come on, come on!

1299
01:32:47,160 --> 01:32:49,000
- Fire control ready?
- Aye, sir.

1300
01:32:49,080 --> 01:32:50,840
- Launcher ready?
- [Launcher] Aye, sir.

1301
01:32:50,920 --> 01:32:52,680
Initiate fire.

1302
01:32:52,760 --> 01:32:54,600
- Freeze! Hold it, sir!
- [Cob] Drop the weapon now!

1303
01:32:54,680 --> 01:32:58,280
Move forward! Move forward!
Move, move, move! Get his pistol!

1304
01:32:58,360 --> 01:33:01,760
- Fire one!
- Number one did not fire, sir.

1305
01:33:03,440 --> 01:33:05,440
Sir, the captain's key
has been removed.

1306
01:33:05,520 --> 01:33:08,240
Hunter.

1307
01:33:09,600 --> 01:33:12,760
- You're a piece of shit.
- Son of a bitch.

1308
01:33:12,840 --> 01:33:14,760
- All right, you and you,
man the forward hatches.
- Aye, sir.

1309
01:33:14,840 --> 01:33:16,640
- [Hunter] You, man the aft hatches.
- Aye, sir.

1310
01:33:16,720 --> 01:33:18,280
We're going up
to periscope depth.

1311
01:33:18,360 --> 01:33:21,680
We're gonna reestablish communications
and get that radio message.

1312
01:33:21,760 --> 01:33:25,320
Now anybody got a problem with that?

1313
01:33:25,400 --> 01:33:28,040
- Chief of the boat,
make your depth 78 feet.
- Aye, aye, sir.

1314
01:33:28,080 --> 01:33:31,200
- Make your depth 78 feet.
Five degree up bubble.
- Mr. Linkletter, man that periscope.

1315
01:33:31,280 --> 01:33:35,040
- Aye sir. Raising number two scope.
- Radio/Conn:

1316
01:33:35,120 --> 01:33:38,840
Mr. Vossler, this is Captain Kirk.
I need warp speed on that radio.

1317
01:33:38,920 --> 01:33:42,600
- Yes, sir.
- Conn/Weapons:

1318
01:33:42,680 --> 01:33:46,080
Russian missiles will have
launch capability in nine minutes.

1319
01:33:47,880 --> 01:33:50,920
- [Radio Static, Beeping]
- Oh, shit!

1320
01:33:50,960 --> 01:33:52,880
- What? What happened?
- Reattach that lead!

1321
01:34:04,680 --> 01:34:08,160
Seventy-eight feet!
At periscope depth, sir!

1322
01:34:08,240 --> 01:34:10,280
- Mr. Linkletter!
- No close contact, sir.

1323
01:34:10,360 --> 01:34:13,760
Very well. Chief of the watch,
raise the VLF radio antenna.

1324
01:34:13,840 --> 01:34:15,720
Raise the VLF antenna.
Aye, sir.

1325
01:34:17,200 --> 01:34:21,320
- VLF antenna coming up!
- [Radio Crew Chattering]

1326
01:34:21,400 --> 01:34:23,960
[Static]

1327
01:34:24,040 --> 01:34:27,560
Conn/Radio: Sir, I think
she's breathing. We're getting close.

1328
01:34:37,320 --> 01:34:38,720
- Halt, sir!
- Shoot me.

1329
01:34:38,800 --> 01:34:41,640
- Shit. Shit.
- I got him.

1330
01:34:41,680 --> 01:34:45,880
I have the conn.

1331
01:34:45,960 --> 01:34:47,880
Give me my missile key.

1332
01:34:56,720 --> 01:34:58,640
Give me the missile key,
Mr. Hunter.

1333
01:35:12,760 --> 01:35:15,880
I'm the commander of this
fucking ship! Give me that goddamn key!

1334
01:35:19,880 --> 01:35:24,600
Conn/Weapons: Russian missiles will have
launch capability in seven minutes.

1335
01:35:25,720 --> 01:35:28,120
Conn/Radio: Sir!

1336
01:35:30,960 --> 01:35:32,800
Radio/Conn!

1337
01:35:32,880 --> 01:35:36,160
Captain/Radio: Vossler, sir. She's
breathing again! We are really close!

1338
01:35:36,240 --> 01:35:38,600
You got three minutes, Vossler.

1339
01:35:38,680 --> 01:35:41,320
- Three minutes and counting!
- Yes, sir.

1340
01:35:43,760 --> 01:35:46,600
You got three minutes.

1341
01:35:53,040 --> 01:35:55,240
[Panels Beeping, Radio Static]

1342
01:35:55,320 --> 01:35:58,640
- Come on.
- [Static Continues]

1343
01:36:14,600 --> 01:36:18,560
[Radioman] Come on, Vossler. Come on,
come on. Keep it going, keep it going.

1344
01:36:18,640 --> 01:36:20,840
[Static Continues]

1345
01:36:24,120 --> 01:36:26,920
Speaking of horses...

1346
01:36:27,000 --> 01:36:29,480
did you ever see
those Lipizzaner stallions?

1347
01:36:30,520 --> 01:36:31,800
What?

1348
01:36:31,880 --> 01:36:34,760
From Portugal.

1349
01:36:34,840 --> 01:36:37,160
The Lipizzaner stallions.

1350
01:36:37,240 --> 01:36:39,880
The most highly trained horses
in the world. They're all white.

1351
01:36:41,720 --> 01:36:44,440
Yes, sir.

1352
01:36:44,520 --> 01:36:48,520
"Yes, sir" you're aware
they're all white...

1353
01:36:48,600 --> 01:36:50,440
or "Yes, sir" you've seen them?

1354
01:36:51,640 --> 01:36:54,280
Yes, sir, I've seen them.

1355
01:36:54,360 --> 01:36:57,320
Yes, sir, I'm aware
that they're all white.

1356
01:36:57,400 --> 01:37:01,800
They're not from Portugal;
they're from Spain...

1357
01:37:01,880 --> 01:37:05,160
and at birth, they're not white;
they're black.

1358
01:37:06,520 --> 01:37:08,520
Sir.

1359
01:37:08,600 --> 01:37:10,760
I didn't know that.

1360
01:37:10,840 --> 01:37:13,360
But they are from Portugal.

1361
01:37:15,920 --> 01:37:17,800
- [Vossler Panting]
- Come on, Vossler. Come on.

1362
01:37:17,840 --> 01:37:22,240
- Yes. Yes.
- Come on. Come on. You got it.

1363
01:37:22,320 --> 01:37:24,840
[Chuckling]

1364
01:37:24,920 --> 01:37:29,200
Some of the things they do,
uh, defy belief.

1365
01:37:29,280 --> 01:37:33,120
Their training program
is simplicity itself.

1366
01:37:33,200 --> 01:37:35,680
You just stick
a cattle prod up their ass...

1367
01:37:35,760 --> 01:37:38,080
and you can get a horse
to deal cards.

1368
01:37:38,120 --> 01:37:41,520
[Chuckles]
Simple matter of voltage.

1369
01:37:49,960 --> 01:37:52,920
[Radioman]
You're gonna get it. Come on.

1370
01:37:53,000 --> 01:37:56,040
- [Screen Beeping, Static]
- I almost had it. You saw it.

1371
01:37:56,080 --> 01:38:01,760
Conn/Weapons: Russian missiles will have
launch capability in four minutes.

1372
01:38:04,200 --> 01:38:07,120
- There you go! There you go!
- Ah, shit!

1373
01:38:11,880 --> 01:38:15,400
Look, look, look! Look at it, Vossler!
There we go, there we go!

1374
01:38:15,480 --> 01:38:18,120
- Yes!
- [Beeping]

1375
01:38:18,200 --> 01:38:22,080
[Beeping Continues]

1376
01:38:22,160 --> 01:38:24,840
Conn/Radio:
We are receiving flash traffic.

1377
01:38:24,920 --> 01:38:27,880
Emergency action message. Recommend
alert one. Recommend alert one.

1378
01:38:27,960 --> 01:38:30,400
- Fuck, yeah!
- [Beeping Continues]

1379
01:38:30,480 --> 01:38:34,080
Alert one. Alert one.
Dougherty, Westergaurd, Zimmer.

1380
01:38:34,160 --> 01:38:36,120
- Get that EAM.
- Aye, aye, sir.

1381
01:38:36,200 --> 01:38:38,960
[Beeping Continues]

1382
01:38:39,040 --> 01:38:41,000
God help you
if you're wrong.

1383
01:38:41,080 --> 01:38:45,040
If I'm wrong,
then we're at war.

1384
01:38:45,120 --> 01:38:47,160
God help us all.

1385
01:38:57,920 --> 01:39:01,480
Sir, we have a properly formatted
emergency action message...

1386
01:39:01,560 --> 01:39:03,400
from the National Command
Authority, sir.

1387
01:39:03,440 --> 01:39:05,560
- Request permission to authenticate.
